        <name>ICE OUT: Community Think-Tank | Hosted by: Good Trouble Indivisible</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT: Community Think-Tank | Hosted by: Good Trouble Indivisible</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, February 24, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Saugatuck-Douglas Library<br>174 Center St<br>Douglas, MI 49406</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>ICE OUT: Community Think-Tank

⏰ 5:30 – 7:30 PM

📍 Saugatuck-Douglas Library   174 Center Street   Douglas, MI 49406

Event Details: 

Please register for this event.

Good Trouble Indivisible&apos;s

ICE OUT: Community Think-Tank is an open, inclusive space for community members to come together to talk, listen, and think critically about what is happening with ICE and immigration enforcement in our cities.

This gathering is not a protest or a lecture. It is a facilitated community conversation designed to:

	•	Share thoughts, concerns, and lived experiences

	•	Discuss the real impacts of ICE activity on families and communities

	•	Brainstorm ideas, actions, and solutions focused on getting ICE out of our cities

	•	Build understanding, solidarity, and community-driven strategies for change

While broader concerns about the current Trump administration and its policies may arise naturally, this Think-Tank will remain intentionally focused on ICE—its role, its impact, and what meaningful community resistance and alternatives can look like.

All are welcome. No prior knowledge or political affiliation is required.
Respectful dialogue and shared humanity are the foundation of this space.

Hosted by: Good Trouble Indivisible
Accessibility: Indoor, seated, warm, and community-centered

This a local Indivisible event!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
