        <name>ICE OUT FOR GOOD &amp; SIGNS OF FASCISM MARCH | ALLEGAN</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT FOR GOOD &amp; SIGNS OF FASCISM MARCH | ALLEGAN</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 4:30 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Allegan City Hall<br>231 Trowbridge St<br>Allegan, MI 49010</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>GOOD TROUBLE INDIVISIBLE’s

ICE OUT FOR GOOD &amp; SIGNS OF FASCISM MARCH | Allegan

👉WE PROVIDE SIGNS, HAND-WARMERS, &amp; RED WHISTLES 👈

👉 PLEASE DRESS IN BLACK 👈

Watch our ICE OUT FOR GOOD March video here:

👉https://www.facebook.com/share/r/1ATArSfNpB/

Watch our SIGNS OF FASCISM March here:

👉https://www.facebook.com/share/v/1GLi2oqvqT/

⏰ 11:30 am—LOOK for Jan’s YELLOW JEEP (in proximity to Allegan City Hall @ 231 Trowbridge St).  

AT THE JEEP: Sign in, pick up your sign, hand-warmers, and a red whistle (in solidarity with Renee Nicole Good to use for Ice sightings). 

⏰ 11:45 am: LINEUP in front of Allegan City Hall for a photo op, receive march instructions, safety tips, and route information.

⏰ NOON: Begin MARCH.

Saturday, February 28th, 11:30 am EST

LOCATION: Allegan City Hall 231 Trowbridge St, Allegan, MI

Please join us in taking a stand against ICE and creating public awareness about the Signs of Fascism happening in the US.

This march is part of Good Trouble Indivisible’s ongoing regional “SIGNS OF FASCISM” and &quot;ICE OUT FOR GOOD&quot; series across West Michigan. This impactful, public awareness march has already taken place three times in Douglas, three times in Saugatuck, in Fennville, Holland, Zeeland, and South Haven — and is now coming to Allegan. Residents are encouraged to join us. (We have combined our ICE OUT FOR GOOD March with our SIGNS OF FASCISM March.)

Good Trouble Indivisible invites you to participate in one of our most powerful nonviolent actions: a silent performance March called SIGNS OF FASCISM will be our first lap through the Allegan downtown area. The second lap of our March through the downtown will represent ICE OUT FOR GOOD.

Participants walk silently, in the first lap of our SIGNS OF FASCISM MARCH, single file, through downtown — dressed in all black — each carrying a stark black-and-white sign naming one warning sign of authoritarianism in America today.

A slow heartbeat drum sets the pace. No chanting. No shouting. No confrontation. Eyes straight ahead. The quiet seriousness of a funeral procession sets the mood and is emulated by the all-black clothing that we all wear.

The second lap, representing ICE OUT FOR GOOD, will duplicate the first lap’s style and demeanor.

All signs are provided at the start of the march. Signs are two-sided. The FASCISM signs are black. The flip side for ICE OUT is white.

This is a peaceful, disciplined visibility action designed to make people pause, reflect, and see what is happening in our country. Our March is known for its impact on public awareness. We intend to both raise public awareness of ICE violence and human rights violations, and the indications of fascism in the Trump administration.

⸻

EVENT SCHEDULE

🕦 11:30 AM — Check-in &amp; choose your sign

🕚 11:45 AM — Line-up, photos, marching instructions, route overview &amp; safety briefing.

🕛 12:00–1:00 PM — Silent march. 2 laps.

⸻

WHAT TO EXPECT

🔹 Silent, single-file march (2 laps downtown)

🔹 Dress code: All black

🔹 Slow heartbeat drum to guide the pace

🔹 Calm, peaceful, disciplined tone

🔹 A powerful visual defense of democracy

⸻

REGISTRATION REQUIRED

⚠️ Limited spots — registration is required. This is a structured performance action with a limited number of signs and positions.

⸻

We see the signs of fascism. and the inhumane treatment of everyone, by ICE.

We refuse to look away.
 
Democracy and human rights are worth fighting for.

Join us. Be seen. Be counted. Be Good Trouble.

⸻

ABOUT GOOD TROUBLE INDIVISIBLE

Good Trouble Indivisible (GTI) is a Saugatuck and Douglas–based grassroots advocacy organization committed to nonviolent action, free speech, and democratic accountability. GTI is a Michigan nonprofit corporation, taking a stand for human rights, our democracy, and the rule of law.

Good Trouble Indivisible is an active, organized, and ongoing group 
—not a one-time event— with a strong track record of over 100 consistent community actions.

Our work includes:

✔️ Meet Us on the Bridge protests — held repeatedly across Saugatuck, Douglas, and surrounding communities

✔️ Chalk-the-Walks visibility actions — conducted in multiple towns as part of ongoing free speech advocacy 

✔️ Signs of Fascism silent performance marches — successfully held in Douglas, Saugatuck, Fennville, Holland, Zeeland, and South Haven.

✔️  Ice Out For Good silent performance Marches — successfully held in Zeeland, Saugatuck, South Haven, and Douglas.

✔️ Free Speech Pop-Up protests — conducted at Saugatuck and Douglas Town Halls

✔️ Santa &amp; Elves holiday ICE OUT Protests

✔️ Community Think-Tanks 

✔️ ICE OUT Community Think-Tanks

✔️  ICE OUT FOR GOOD VIGILS to honor lives lost and our crumbling democracy

✔️ Media coverage and interviews with local television and print news outlets 

✔️ Sign making workshops

✔️Volunteer Open Houses

OVER 120 PUBLIC ACTION EVENTS THROUGHOUT WEST MICHIGAN

* Public Actions do not include dozens upon dozens of GTI&apos;s regularly held monthly Leadership Council meetings, quarterly Board of Directors meetings, Project Management meetings, Volunteer Organizing meetings, Onboarding, Training, or one-on-one meetings, which all support our long-term organizing. 

Good Trouble Indivisible shows up — week after week — to defend democracy, human rights, the rule of law, free speech, and the right to peaceful protest as we build a civic resistance ecosystem.

ADDITIONAL EVENTS LAUNCHING SOON

