    <Placemark>
        <name>Reimagine Resistance - The Work of Illumination</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Reimagine Resistance - The Work of Illumination</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 23, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 1:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Brix Cider<br>119 S 2nd St<br>Mount Horeb, WI 53572</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> WisDems</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Resistance is not a knee jerk response to alarm. Resistance does not mean hardening ourselves into a dark, protective shell. Resistance isn’t always about pushing back louder and harder.
Resistance can be about walking into dark places and finding a way to shine some light even where it seems impossible.
We will gather for an evening of shared reflection around the realities and human impact of ICE and immigration enforcement. The night will include music and poetry as well as some informative guest speakers.
We are grateful to welcome Dan Zimmerman, coordinator of the Dane Sanctuary Coalition, and David Couper, retired Madison Police Chief and pastor, among confirmed speakers.
There will also be an open mic for those who wish to share information, stories, questions, or creative expression.
This is not a rally.
It is not a debate.
It is not a performance of righteousness.
It is a space to illuminate what feels overwhelming, and to remember that even when the dark feels impenetrable, a small light still matters.
All are welcome.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/897077/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
