    <Placemark>
        <name>End ICE Detention at Miami Correctional Facility Rally</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>End ICE Detention at Miami Correctional Facility Rally</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Common Ground Midtown Church<br>4550 N Illinois St<br>Indianapolis, IN 46208</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Central Indiana</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>A broad coalition of organizations (listed below) have come together to call on Governor Mike Braun to End ICE Detention at the Miami Correctional Facility. 

Approximately 600 ICE detainees are being held at this prison under terrible conditions. Many ICE detainees are being held unconstitutionally but lack the resources to hire an attorney to represent them in federal court. Over 70% of ICE detainees have no criminal record and over 95% of ICE detainees have never been accused of a violent crime. 

Hoosiers believe in the importance of family. Our state must stop contributing to the unnecessary and cruel separation of families and traumatization of children. 

We will gather at Common Ground Midtown church at 4pm on Sunday, February 22nd. The address is 4550 N. Illinois Street. There will be a short program to center everyone on the meaning and tone of this public witness action. We will then proceed to the Governor&apos;s Mansion, one block east at 46th and N. Meridian Street, with chanting and song at approximately 4:45pm and will remain until 6:00pm. 

If you wish to bring a sign, please keep your signs &quot;family-friendly.&quot; 

Examples include:
&quot;End ICE Detention @ Miami Correctional&quot;  
&quot;Gov. Braun: Do the Right Thing&quot;  
&quot;Love Thy Neighbor&quot;  
&quot;Close the Concentration Camp&quot;  
&quot;Invest in Our Communities Not ICE&quot;  
&quot;Build Affordable Housing Not Concentration Camps&quot;  
&quot;Hoosiers United in Love.&quot; 

Co-Sponsors Include: 
Indiana Conference of the United Methodist Church 
Peace Church Coalition (Quakers, Mennonites, and Church of the Brethren) 
Indiana NETWORK Advocates Team
Indivisible Central Indiana
Fishers Resists
Indiana Undocumented Youth Alliance
Westside Indy Indivisible Resistance Movement
Indiana Peace and Justice Center
Brethren Building Beloved Community (B3C)
Indiana Resistance
Indy Liberation Center</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/896832/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
