    <Placemark>
        <name>Kick ICE out of Indy Airport!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Kick ICE out of Indy Airport!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 1:00 PM UTC - 2:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Indianapolis International Airport<br>7800 Col. H. Weir Cook Memorial Dr<br>Indianapolis, IN 46241</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Westside Indy Indivisible Resistance Movement</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Tell the Indianapolis Airport Authority (IAA) to kick ICE out of our airport!

Since July 2025, three ICE flights per week have stopped at the Indianapolis Airport to pick up our kidnapped neighbors and transport them to the government’s deportation hub in Alexandria, Louisiana. 

Here is an article with more info on the Indy flights:
https://mirrorindy.org/indianapolis-airport-ice-flights-immigration-detainees-donald-trump/

Learn more about nationwide ICE flights here: https://humanrightsfirst.org/ice-flight-monitor/

The IAA board meets monthly, and these meetings are open to the public. So we’re showing up at the February 20 meeting to show the IAA, the public, and most of all our immigrant neighbors that HOOSIERS SEE WHAT’S HAPPENING AND WE CONDEMN IT.

We will meet in the Civic Plaza (the big atrium with restaurants on the Departures level) at 7:45am. From there we will go as a group to the airport board room (Room 11T.413).

Print and bring signs of solidarity to be uniform (print outs here https://tinyurl.com/bdznbj9n) telling the IAA that while immigrants are welcome here, ICE IS NOT! You may also wish to come prepared with brief anti-ICE pro-immigrant remarks, in case the meeting agenda includes time for public comments.

This is a nonviolent and peaceful rally; we will follow meeting rules and not disrupt procedures.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/901478/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
