<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>No Kings! No Crowns!

Now is the time for even more people to raise their voices and be visible in their resistance.Politicians do take notice of these, large peaceful, non-violent protests. The Trump administration is lashing out even more with ICE aggression and voter suppression because they know they are losing their support. 

Help us double the number of people we will gather in Houdini Plaza and along College avenue on March 28 3 pm to 5pm. Raise your voice, show your signs of outrage,  hear some speakers, join in chants, enjoy the enthusiasm of like-minded people .It will be loud.  It will be fun.  

This protest is supported by many local organizations. Look for their announcements and ours of many events leading to this momentous rally. 
Fox Valley Indivisible, Forward Fox Valley(Indivisible), Hate Free Outagamie, National Organization of Women (NOW), League of Women Voters, Outagamie Dems, NEW Resist.
*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
