        <name>Indivisible SCI General Meeting Feb. 2026</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Indivisible SCI General Meeting Feb. 2026</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 7:45 PM UTC - 9:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Monroe County Public Library - Ellettsville Branch<br>600 W Temperance St<br>Ellettsville, IN 47429</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible South Central Indiana</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**Our February meeting will now feature special guest speaker Sheriff Ruben Marté, rescheduled from our snowed-out January meeting.** 

The &quot;Refugees 101&quot; training from Exodus Refugee Immigration originally planned for the February meeting will be rescheduled for sometime in March, exact date TBD.

Please arrive by 2:45pm so we can get everyone signed in and start the meeting promptly at 3:00pm.

### Guest Speaker
We will be joined by Sheriff Ruben Marté to hear his vision for law enforcement in Monroe County. Marté has been protecting the rights of our immigrant neighbors by refusing to honor unconstitutional ICE holds.

### In-Meeting Action
Our friends from Exodus Refugee Immigration, Inc. will update us on immigration-related legislation currently active in the Indiana statehouse and actions you can take to support good bills and oppose those that harm our immigrant neighbors.

### ISCI Photography &amp; Video Policy
ISCI may take photos or videos at meetings and events to document, share, and promote our activities. When taking photos or videos, ISCI representatives will do their best to seek explicit consent before photographing individuals with their faces or names visible. We ask all participants taking personal photos or videos to seek consent as well and respect the wishes of those who do not want to be photographed or recorded. **Please note that in public settings, including protests, there is always the possibility of being identifiably photographed.** Ultimately, the responsibility for protecting our identity lies with each of us individually. If you are concerned about being photographed or recorded during Indivisible activities, we strongly encourage you to cover your face and other identifiable features.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/888068/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
