        <name>No Kings III</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>No Kings III</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Curwood Castle Park<br>400 W Main St<br>Owosso, MI 48867</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Shiawassee County Democratic Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The Shiawassee County Democratic Party is organizing a third No Kings peaceful protest to stand in solidarity against the recent ICE violence, detentions and unlawful deportation of immigrants in the United States. We encourage individuals, families and groups to join us to voice concerns about the reduction of services to vulnerable citizens and the need to protect and uphold voting rights for everyone. Our country is not ruled by kings or dictators- it is a democracy. We uphold our local, state and national laws that uphold our Democracy and protect the rights of all. Join us at the Curwood Castle Park for a short presentation and walk peacefully to M21 on the bridge and sidewalk in front of and across from the Owosso City Hall.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904683/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
