    <Placemark>
        <name>ICE Out of Oakland County!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out of Oakland County!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 2:30 PM UTC - 4:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Courthouse South Entrance<br>1200 N Telegraph<br>Pontiac, MI 48341</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> NE Oakland Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## 𝐎𝐚𝐤𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐂𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐭𝐲 — 𝐥𝐞𝐭’𝐬 𝐤𝐞𝐞𝐩 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐨𝐧 𝟐/𝟏𝟗.


At the last meeting, more than 100 residents showed up. Voices from across the county were heard loud and clear. That energy mattered.


𝐍𝐨𝐰 𝐰𝐞 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐤𝐞𝐞𝐩 𝐢𝐭 𝐠𝐨𝐢𝐧𝐠. 𝐒𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐮𝐩, 𝐄𝐦𝐚𝐢𝐥, 𝐂𝐚𝐥𝐥, 𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐞!


🗓 Board of Commissioners Meeting

📍 Thursday, Feb 19, 9:30 AM

🎤 Public comment: 𝟑 𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐮𝐭𝐞𝐬 𝐩𝐞𝐫 𝐬𝐩𝐞𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐫

𝐓𝐨𝐨𝐥𝐤𝐢𝐭: https://rb.gy/2m13zp (new email templates, phone scripts, SM assets)


If you’re able, take your 3 minutes and speak. Share why protecting our neighbors and keeping county buildings safe matters to you.


If public speaking isn’t your thing, that’s okay — 𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐛𝐞𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐦 𝐦𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐬 𝐚 𝐝𝐢𝐟𝐟𝐞𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞. A full chamber sends a message.


This is how change happens: we organize, we show up, and we don’t disappear after one meeting.


From Ferndale to Oxford, from Troy to Milford — Oakland County residents care. Let’s show it again.


See you Thursday!


𝐓𝐨𝐨𝐥𝐤𝐢𝐭: https://rb.gy/2m13zp (new email templates, phone scripts, SM assets)</p>
