        <name>ICE OUT</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Sidewalk in front of John Muir<br>Stewart Circle &amp; South 17th Avenue<br>Wausau, WI 54401</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Across the country, ICE and Border Patrol continue to escalate abusive and unaccountable enforcement—conducting raids without transparency, using excessive force against protesters, and undermining basic constitutional and human rights. Communities have witnessed federal agents targeting families, intimidating legal observers, and operating with near-total impunity, fueling fear rather than safety.

These actions are not isolated—they are part of a growing pattern that demands public resistance. Showing up matters. When we take to the streets, we send a clear message that our communities reject violence, secrecy, and the tearing apart of families. Join the ICE OUT protest and stand for dignity, accountability, and justice.
This action is a public call for humane policies that keep families together and respect the dignity of all people in our community.

We will also be collecting non-perishable food items to donate to Neighbor’s Place of Wausau, supporting local families in need.

All are welcome. Peaceful, lawful, and community-centered.

This a local Indivisible event!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
