        <name>Northern Michigan People’s Hearing: Ice Storm Impacts, One Year On</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Northern Michigan People’s Hearing: Ice Storm Impacts, One Year On</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Treetops Resort<br>3962 Wilkinson Rd<br>Gaylord, MI 49735</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Climate Action Campaign</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us in Gaylord for a People’s Hearing bringing together community members, local leaders, and environmental experts from across Northern Michigan.

One year after the devastating March 2025 ice storms, families, farmers, and small business owners are still navigating a long road to recovery—from repairing property and rebuilding livelihoods to preparing for future extreme weather storms. 

This People’s Hearing creates space for Northern Michigan residents to share what they lived through and speak directly with elected officials about what their communities need moving forward.

The event is designed as a community gathering, with time to connect with neighbors, Michigan-based nonprofit organizations, and local leaders. Food and drinks will be available. Members of the press will be in attendance to help elevate community voices and stories beyond the room.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/887955/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
