        <name>What You Need to Know About ICE</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>What You Need to Know About ICE</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Ohio Progressive Action Leaders</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## What You Need to Know About ICE:
##
- Your Rights

- Your Risks

- How to Resist

- How We Win

_Join us for an important, informative, and empowering conversation with Steve Volk, Professor of History Emeritus at Oberlin College_ in Ohio, who has been active in immigration issues for 20 years.

**The Trump-Stephen Miller immigration policies are designed around cruelty - to prevent immigrants from coming, encourage immigrants to &quot;self-deport,&quot; and put those who remain into a perpetual state of panic and fear. What they didn&apos;t count on was that performances of cruelty can also create acts of resistance and opposition.**

In this Zoom forum, we&apos;ll talk about **what rights EVERYONE in the country, regardless of immigration status, enjoys; how they have been challenged; and how we are fighting back.** We&apos;ll cover the rights we have when protesting, and the multiple ways opposition to Trump&apos;s policies has grown, ultimately producing the massive -- and victorious -- resistance movement on the frozen streets of Minneapolis. Finally, we&apos;ll explore what is likely to come next for Trump and the opposition movement.

There will be time for questions. Please share yours when registering for the Zoom.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904580/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
