        <name>Protect Our Neighbors: Restore MN</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Protect Our Neighbors: Restore MN</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Minnesota State Capitol<br>75 Rev Dr Martin Luther King Jr Boulevard.<br>Saint Paul, MN 55155</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Twin Cities</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join fellow Minnesotans as we demand our state leadership and Republicans stand with the people of Minnesota amid the federal occupation AND take action to restore and heal our state and communities from the carnage caused by Trump&apos;s ICE.

It&apos;s from 1:00 to 3:00 at the MN State Capitol Rotunda. The program will start at 1:30. There will be opportunities to connect with your state legislators too.

Indivisible Twin Cities is partnering with ISAIAH/Faith in Minnesota and many other organizations who are ready to take action to restore and heal our state.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/901931/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
