        <name>Minnesota families: caucus to get ICE out of schools!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Minnesota families: caucus to get ICE out of schools!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 12:30 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> TakeAction Minnesota</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Elections f**king matter, and everyday people like us have a powerful role to play in determining which candidates get a huge leg up in their race. From school board members to elected prosecutors to the governor, we deserve politicians who actually act to get ICE out of our schools, and who deliver the housing for all, food support, universal pre-K, and universal health care -- and more! -- that our families and communities deserve. 

We&apos;re getting trained in how to get politicians to deliver.

At this training you&apos;ll learn and practice how to show up where your voice has outsize power: precinct caucuses. (&quot;Precinct caucus&quot; is a gatekeeping phrase that means &quot;neighborhood meeting.&quot; These meetings happen all over Minnesota the evening of Feb 3, 2026.) 

The decisions everyday people make at this meeting determine which candidates get &quot;endorsed&quot; by a political party -- and get all all the votes, resources, and support that come with an endorsement. 

We&apos;ll learn what precinct caucus is, why it matters, and how we can show up to make sure that only #FamiliesOverBillionaires and #ICEout candidates get what they need to run competitive races.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/781816/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
