<h3>Citizens Bank:  Stop Funding Cruelty</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 4:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Citizens Bank<br>1801 Murray Avenue<br>Pittsburgh, PA 15217</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Indivisible Regent Square in a peaceful protest outside Citizens Bank in Squirrel Hill!
NOTE: THIS IS A NEW LOCATION FIR US! We will no longer be at the Swissvale branch!

Citizens Bank, through Citizens Financial Group, has long financed private prison operators like The GEO Group despite decades of abuse, neglect, and exploitation. Right here in PA, GEO runs the Moshannon Valley Processing Center, the largest ICE detention site in the Northeast. 

Join Indivisibles across Pennsylvania to shine a light on the Moshannon Valley Processing Center and to demand that Citizens Bank stop funding cruelty.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
