        <name>Ice Out of Minnesota 6.0</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Ice Out of Minnesota 6.0</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>1300 W St Germain St<br>St. Cloud, MN 56301</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Americans for Democracy</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>After five powerful weeks of protests pushing back against ICE’s presence in Minnesota, we are coming together again this weekend. These actions have been about more than protest — they’ve been about building community, standing in solidarity, and refusing to stay silent.
Join us as we continue to push back, support one another, and show that Minnesota will not tolerate fear or violence in our communities.
Stand with us. Bring a friend. This week we&apos;re encouraging signs love and solidarity for one another while showing ICE we are a strong community and they&apos;re not welcome here! Let’s keep showing up. This Saturday 11- 1:00 p.m.

Alongside the ICE Out of Minnesota protest, we will be collecting food for immigrant families who are afraid to leave their homes due to ICE activity and the risk of arrest or deportation. Your donations help keep our neighbors safe and fed.

Some of the items needed-
Baby items- diapers of all sizes, baby food and wipes
Flour, sugar, baking soda, cooking oil, spices 
Peanut butter, canned meats 
Fresh fruits and vegetables
Coffee and tea 
Rice and canned goods

The donations will be collected at the welcome table.
You may park in the library parking lot.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/897553/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
