        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Know Your Rights Presentation and Q&amp;A</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Blacksburg Library<br>200 Miller St SW<br>Blacksburg, VA 24060</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for a Know Your Rights Presentation given by Immigration Attorney Mikhayla Adkins, Esq.

Mikhayla is an Immigration Attorney who has a deep commitment to serving the immigrant community and has been focused on naturalization and derivative citizenship, as well as experience in family based immigration, DACA, religious immigration, employment based immigration, asylum, human rights, and international law. In addition to direct immigration services, I have also done work advocating for the abolition of immigration detention, and tracking the human and legal rights abuses found in the immigration incarceration system. 

Mikhayla has generously offered to give a KYR presentation to NRV Indivisible members and the community!

    -Basic overview of Due Process / Constitutional Rights
 
    -Tips for when ICE comes knocking, including how to distinguish an ICE warrant from a signed judicial warrant 

    -Q+A / Organizing Tips 

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/889143/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
