        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Cards for a Cause: Contact Your Reps</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 25, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Webster&apos;s Bookstore Cafe<br>133 E Beaver Ave<br>State College, PA 16801</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Keystone Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Ice Out + Protect Our Right to Vote + Represent Your Constituents

On Wednesday, February 25th, we will be gathering together at Webster&apos;s from 6:00-8:00pm to write postcards to our elected representatives - receiving a large volume of postcards is hard for them to ignore!

We will provide postcards with a variety of messages, mailing addresses for our reps, and scripts for that cover multiple issues, asking our reps to use their power to protect our communities. Follow our suggestions, or write your own message! Copies of the scripts and addresses will be available for you to take home and share with others.

There is no fee to participate in this event. If you are able, we gratefully appreciate if you can pitch in for stamp money.

This is a nonpartisan event hosted by members of Keystone Indivisible. Learn more at KeystoneIndivisible.org .</p>
