        <name>A Time to Remember and A Time to Sing, a candlelight vigil</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>A Time to Remember and A Time to Sing, a candlelight vigil</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Lafayette Park<br>Corner of Fourth and Porter Street<br>Watkins Glen, NY 14891</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This a local Indivisible event!

We will gather together to remember those who have died in ICE Custody or while peacefully protesting. We will have a short candle light vigil march from the corner of Porter Street and 4th Street, at Lafayette Park to St. James Episcopal Church in Watkins Glen. Once we reach the church, you will be offered a warm drink and cookies on your way to your seat.  We will then hold a memorial candle lighting ceremony.  At the conclusion of the ceremony, we will raise our voices in song with the help of Joe Chicone and perhaps others. 

It is our hope that this ceremony will give us an opportunity to acknowledge our distress and grief over the loss of human life at the hands of ICE.  We hope that each participant will go home feeling comforted in knowing that others share their pain and distress.  We also hope that each participant will walk away, feeling inspired and feeling a renewed sense of community...


*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
