        <name>Know Your Rights: Responding to ICE Presence in Frederick County Schools</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Know Your Rights: Responding to ICE Presence in Frederick County Schools</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, February 24, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>57 Thomas Johnson Dr<br>Frederick, MD 21702</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Maryland State Education Association</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>In partnership with community organizations and leaders, this event will provide timely information and practical guidance for educators in Frederick County. Topics include updates on ICE activity in the county, FCPS protocols related to ICE, how to recognize ICE and respond appropriately, and ways educators can help ensure students get safely to and from school. The session will also cover how school communities can support families impacted by ICE arrests or deportations, along with clear next steps and opportunities to get involved.</p>
