        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>IND Cobb presents ACLU Know Your Rights (KYR) and Capitol Observer training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 10, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Kirkwood Presbyterian Church<br>618 Acworth Due West Rd NW<br>Kennesaw, GA 30152</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Cobb</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>ACLU of GA is bringing the training to us on Tuesday, Mar 10 from 7-9p. 

The first hour will cover Know Your Rights (KYR) training as it relates to protesting, if you are stopped by the police, and how to record ICE interactions safely and accurately.

The second hour will cover Capitol Observer training. When lawmakers are in session, ACLU of Georgia&apos;s capitol observers are there to protect free speech and democracy. 

Come at 7p and stay for one or both sessions, or come at 8p for the 2nd session. Just come!

Please visit ACLU of GA webpage for need to know info: https://www.acluga.org/prga/

**We will be meeting in the basement of the church. The entrance is around back. Please park back here in the wooded area or in the small lot off the side entrance of the church. Do not enter the church from the main entrance or the ones off the main parking lot. Thank you.**</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903220/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
