        <name>How to win in urban North Carolina</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>How to win in urban North Carolina</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 23, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Swing Blue Alliance</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>North Carolina has multiple, fast-growing urban areas - the Triangle, the Triad, Greater Mecklenburg and more.  Hear leading community organizers who are building power and winning elections in these areas.  

How have they organized to stop ICE deportations and resist federal assaults on social programs?  What are the prospects in 2026 to win legislative seats and county commission majorities? How does their work set the stage for statewide wins? 

Moderator - Sen. Woodson Bradley (D-Mecklenburg) - pictured above
Speakers: 
* Marlene Martinez, Organizing Director, SiembraNC 
* Olivia Zalecki, Deputy Director, NC Asian Americans Together in Action
* Jenn Frye, Co-Director, Carolina Federation</p>
