    <Placemark>
        <name>Ice out of Our Schools!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Ice out of Our Schools!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 8:30 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>American Friends Services Committee (AFSC)<br>711 Catherine St SW<br>Atlanta, GA 30310</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Working Families Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join the WFPeaches and Raising Comrades for a training and discussion about how kids and families can support our kids and the immigrant communities in their schools and day cares. 

### Event details
Calling all parents, caregivers, and allies of children heartbroken by ICE harming our communities! Are you struggling to talk as a family about ICE? Or maybe you have vulnerable members in your school or community that you’re looking to support. Are you equipped with a plan if ICE comes to your school or day care facility?
 
Join us at 3:30 p.m. on Feb. 22, as we spend an afternoon addressing these topics and more. This will be a safe space for parents, kids, and community members to discuss concerns, ask questions, and learn how to take action. You will walk away with tools to start organizing within your school or day care community. 

Location details will be sent prior to the event.

### Will childcare be provided?
Bring the kids along! This training is intended for all ages, so child care will not be present. We kindly ask all attendees to participate to the extent they can, taking breaks when needed.

### About Raising Comrades
Raising Comrades is an Atlanta-based anti-capitalist collective of caregivers supporting children and one another in nonviolent resistance. Formed in 2024, they are made up of parents, guardians, aunties, babysitters, educators and, most importantly, kids. They plan together and protest together—including hosting know-your-rights and street medic trainings, developing checklists and curricula for child-friendly protests and rallies, and providing childcare for grown-ups desiring to attend riskier actions.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/902052/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
