        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Meet &amp; Greet with Janeese Lewis George!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 6, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Shanklin Hall<br>2325 18th St NW<br>Washington, DC 20009</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Janeese for DC Mayor</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us on Thursday March 5th for a Meet &amp; Greet with Mayoral Candidate Janeese Lewis George!

Learn why so many of us are strong supporters of her campaign, which will bring progressive leadership at a time when DC needs it most. And stay for a night of Hip Hip, Afrobeats, and Latin music!

WHO IS SHE? Currently the Councilmember for Ward 4, she is a 3rd generation Washingtonian, proud graduate of DC Public Schools and Howard Law School and a DC Assistant Attorney General before being elected to DC Council. So yes, she&apos;s got the cred and experience to lead DC.

WHAT DOES SHE CARE ABOUT? Probably lots of the same things you do: climate change, affordable housing, universal childcare, good jobs, safer streets, quality education, and ENDING COLLABORATION WITH ICE! Learn more at www.janeesefordc.com

WHAT&apos;S THIS ABOUT MUSIC? We&apos;ll have some DJs spinning Hip Hop, Afrobeats, and Latin music until 10pm, when we hand it off to Shanklin Hall&apos;s Afro music night!

Hosted by: Emelie Jimenez, Maria Mendez, Leon Scott, Troy Collazo, Raha Wala, Claire McAndrew, Rebecca Lee Nelson, Annie Weinberg, Becca Watts, Julia Skapik, Dana Brown, Lauren Carlisle, Dave Chandrasekaran</p>
