        <name>Rally NO ICE prison in Social Circle</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Rally NO ICE prison in Social Circle</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 8, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>100 Court St<br>Monroe, GA 30655</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Georgia District 10</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Indivisible Boldly Blue and IndivisibleGA10 invite you to join in saying **No ICE prisons in Social Circle!** at this peaceful rally in front of the historic Walton County Courthouse across from Congressman Mike Collins&apos;s district office. Other co-sponsoring groups include Indivisible ATL, Indivisible North Metro Atlanta, Indivisible Necessary Trouble, Indivisible Cobb, and 50501 Georgia.

Collins claims to have a close relationship with ICE officials. We urge him to use his influence to stop the creation of the largest federal prison in Georgia - *housing 8,500-10,000 prisoners* - out of a warehouse in a small town of 5,000. The detention center is wrong for many reasons: it would triple the population of Social Circle, placing harmful stress on the town&apos;s water, sewer, and public safety systems. It is within a mile of the new elementary school. 

**This warehouse-turned-prison must be stopped!** Bring your signs and voices to the rally.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904715/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
