        <name>Free Leqaa Kordia: Community Letter-Writing + Awareness Event</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Free Leqaa Kordia: Community Letter-Writing + Awareness Event</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Elkridge Branch - Howard County Library System<br>6540 Washington Blvd<br>Elkridge, MD 21075</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Howard County for a Free Palestine</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Leqaa Kordia, a Palestinian woman from New Jersey, remains in ICE detention far from her family and community. Join **Howard County for a Free Palestine**, **American Muslims for Palestine - DMV Chapter**, **CAIR-MD**, **Our Revolution Howard County**, and **Howard County Muslim Alliance** to learn about her case, the broader pattern of political repression targeting Palestine solidarity, and how we can pressure elected officials to act.

This will be a practical, community-centered event: we’ll share updates, review concrete action steps, and write letters to Leqaa to let her know she is not alone. Letters will be collected and delivered.

Agenda:

- Brief case overview + latest updates
- Action steps: contacting federal officials and escalating pressure
- Letter-writing to Leqaa (materials provided; feel free to bring your own)
- Community discussion + next actions

What to bring:

- A pen/marker (we’ll have extras)
- A friend


*This is not a Howard County Library System (HCLS) sponsored event.*</p>
