<h3>Know Your Right Canvass 2.0, Glen Burnie</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 25, 2026 at 4:15 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>East Moon Asian Bistro<br>7400 Governor Ritchie Hwy suite A<br>Glen Burnie, MD 21061</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Glen Burnie</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Our second Glen Burnie canvass will reach out to businesses with information about the rights of individuals and employers when dealing with ICE. As the events of December 24th showed, ICE is getting more active in Anne Arundel County. It&apos;s vital that people know their rights and how to prepare for interactions with ICE and other immigration agencies.

If you haven&apos;t done a KYR canvass before, no worries! We&apos;ll have a brief training before going out, and we will work in teams. These canvasses get very positive responses from the community overall. In the few cases where people are not open to our message, we simply move on!

We will meet at a Glen Burnie restaurant- the location will be provided when you sign up.  The restaurant staff has asked that we arrive at 11:15 so they have time to set up.  Hope to see you there!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
