        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>CRI Immigration Meeting: KYR and Rapid Response Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 23, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Collingswood Public Library<br>771 Haddon Ave<br>Collingswood, NJ 08108</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Cooper River Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This meeting will review fundamental rights and what your rights are when responding to an ICE incident.

Rapid response training aims to connect you to your local immigrant support network.

Learn who to call if you see ICE in the streets.

Learn about your rights to document and bear witness to injustice.

Learn what you can do to help families being racially profiled, detained, &amp; targeted by racial profiling at the hands of immigration enforcement operations right now.

