        <name>Citizens vs. Citizens Bank--Stop Funding ICE Detention Centers!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Citizens vs. Citizens Bank--Stop Funding ICE Detention Centers!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>2030 NJ-70<br>Cherry Hill Township, NJ 08002</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Cooper River Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Citizens Bank is a major lender to Geo Group and Core Civic, both of whom run private prisons and detention facilities like Delany Hall in Newark, Elizabeth Detention in Elizabeth NJ, and Moshannon in Pennsylvania.  

After ICE abducts our friends and neighbors, Delaney Hall, Elizabeth Detention Center and Moshannon are where most of them are taken. There, they are subject to abuses such inhumane living conditions, severe medical neglect, abusive treatment from guards, poor food/water quality and more all while these corporations make record profits off of the suffering of human beings.  

This must stop.  

Join us in peacefully protesting their complicity.  Bring signs specific to this action so we can spread the word!

For example: 
--De-ICE Citizens Bank
--Cages aren&apos;t Communities 
--Stop Financing Ice Prisons
--Citizen Bank-Cut Ties with ICE Prisons
 

Bring your signs and spread the word!



PS.  When parking, let’s spread out in the lots behind Citizen’s Bank.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/900344/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
