        <name>Spanish Conversation Club</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Spanish Conversation Club</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 5:30 PM UTC - 6:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Camden County Library Voorhees<br>203 Laurel Rd<br>Voorhees Township, NJ 08043</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Cooper River Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for a fun and relaxed gathering where we practice speaking Spanish in a supportive, judgment-free environment! Whether you&apos;re a beginner, intermediate, or fluent speaker, this club is all about building confidence, improving fluency, and connecting with others who share a love for the language.

What to expect:
Casual conversation practice in small groups
Themed prompts and games to spark discussion
Cultural tidbits from Spanish-speaking countries

Cooper River Indivisible is doing a food collection to support the families in Camden affected by ICE, plus the children in the school, who are also needed supplemental snacks. Please consider bringing a few of the items below to our next meeting: Rice
Limes
Diapers (adult/kids) Beans (Dry or canned)
Lemons
