        <name>Roxbury, NJ Says No to ICE Detention</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Roxbury, NJ Says No to ICE Detention</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 25, 2026 at 12:30 AM UTC - 1:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Roxbury Township Town Hall<br>1715 US-46<br>Roxbury Township, NJ 07852</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Bogota Community Defense</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join a community call to action to stop an ICE detention facility from being built in Roxbury, NJ. Show up to the city council meeting to make it clear that all of New Jersey opposes the so called &quot;Amazon warehouse for humans&quot;, and that Roxbury rejects having the detention in their backyard.

Attendees will have the option to use a three-minute public comment slot to speak directly to the council, or you can simply stand with neighbors to demonstrate unified opposition to this project. Your presence matters and visible turnout influences decisions. If you&apos;re planning to speak, please be respectful but assertive. Don&apos;t insult, don&apos;t let the rage out all the way, but let them see that it makes you angry, let them see how this is making you feel. Show them that this is wrong. Together, we are united!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/883096/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
