    <Placemark>
        <name>Melting ICE: Inside the Movement to Protect Sussex County</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Melting ICE: Inside the Movement to Protect Sussex County</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 23, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Lewes Public Library<br>111 Adams Ave<br>Lewes, DE 19958</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Women&apos;s March Sussex</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Women&apos;s March Sussex in-person in Lewes or online as representatives  from the Delaware Coalition for Immigrant Justice share what that organization is doing to support immigrant communities in Sussex County, and how friends and allies can help. Co-presented by Margaret Reyes and Joanne McAfee.

Reyes is a fierce advocate for the Hispanic and immigrant rights communities for two decades. Her experience includes serving as the Social Justice Chair of the Governor’s Advisory Council on Hispanic Affairs, and holding the immigration chair for the Delaware Domestic Violence Coordinating Council, as well as her participation with the Delaware Coalition for Immigrant Justice. Margaret is a retired firefighter and FEMA urban search and rescue task force member with multiple deployments, who has lived primarily in Delaware since 2000. She holds dual citizenship with the United States and Ireland.  

A native Delawarean, McAfee lives near Milford with her husband, Carlos, and their two adult children. After studying Immigration Law at Villanova University, she began working as an immigrant advocate and immigration specialist. For the past five years, she has advocated for reformed immigration policies at both the local and national levels and has co-facilitated discussion groups focused on racial healing and honoring lived experience. She also works closely with Margaret and the Delaware Coalition for Immigrant Justice in Sussex County to spread awareness and support and protect neighbors impacted by ICE operations.

The Delaware Coalition for Immigrant Justice shares information regarding federal immigration enforcement and supports members of the immigrant community adversely affected by these actions. 

Women’s March Sussex – Delaware, an Indivisible group since 2024, is an intersectional and inclusive coalition, promoting active participation in the political process on the local, state, and national levels. Its mission is to empower Sussex County residents through education and civic engagement, equipping them to advocate for issues affecting women. By fostering informed participation, we strive to create a more just, equitable, and sustainable future for women in Sussex County and across Delaware.

Due to limited seating, registration is required. 

To attend online, register here: https://us06web.zoom.us/meeting/register/ZzOSzNwITe6fNtUTritejQ</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/899045/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
