        <name>Kingston: Fight ICE, Stop Billionaires Town Hall with Michelle Hinchey &amp; Sarahana Shrestha</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Kingston: Fight ICE, Stop Billionaires Town Hall with Michelle Hinchey &amp; Sarahana Shrestha</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 11:30 PM UTC - 1:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Senate Garage<br>4 North Front St<br>Kingston, NY 12401</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> For The Many</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>From ICE raids in our communities to an affordability crisis driven by corporate greed, New Yorkers are under attack. 

Join For the Many for a town hall with Assemblymember Sarahana Shrestha &amp; State Senator Michelle Hinchey. At this event, we’ll talk about the fights we’re focused on right now: making New York stop helping ICE, tax the rich, freeze rent upstate, and take over Central Hudson.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/892903/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
