        </Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>Poughkeepsie: Fight ICE, Fight Billionaires Town Hall with Antonio Delgado</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Poughkeepsie: Fight ICE, Fight Billionaires Town Hall with Antonio Delgado</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Cunneen-Hackett Arts Center<br>12 Vassar St<br>Poughkeepsie, NY 12601</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> For The Many</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>From ICE raids in our communities to an affordability crisis driven by corporate greed, New Yorkers are under attack. Governor Hochul has long been one of our biggest obstacles to doing anything about it. 

Antonio Delgado has ended his campaign for Governor, but our fight continues. At this event, we’ll talk about the fights we’re focused on right now: making New York stop helping ICE, tax the rich, freeze rent upstate, and take over Central Hudson.

Come hear directly from Delgado and join our movement to win the future we deserve.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/892904/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
