            <Data name="Organization"><value>Bogota Community Defense</value></Data>
            <Data name="LocationType"><value>exact</value></Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
            <coordinates>-74.0297737,40.8793161,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>Protest Rally</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Protest Rally</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 8:30 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>1715 NJ-35<br>Middletown Township, NJ 07748</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Protest Rally! 

Join Indivisible, Jersey Shore Blue, Middletown Outrage into Action, Shore Area NOW, and MOCA, as we protest against a slew of concerns, including ICE’s illegal detention of immigrants without due process, ICE’s escalation of violence in Minneapolis, the cuts to Medicaid and other essential federal programs, the tax cuts to billionaires, the illegal invasion of Venezuela, and Trump’s threats to Greenland and other countries. Until Rep. Chris Smith and the rest of Congress begins to show genuine congressional oversight and push back against the unconstitutional actions of the Trump administration, we will protest.

Join us Wednesday from 3:30 to dusk in front of Rep. Chris Smith&apos;s Middletown office located at 1715 Route 35! While Chris Smith has abandoned this office, we have not. His office building is just north of the Middletown Post Office on 35. Look for us roadside on the grass in front of the office building&apos;s parking lot. Remember to bring your signs, your flags, and your friends!!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/892357/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
