        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>SAT 2/21 @2: MIDTOWN WEST SIGNS OF SOLIDARITY-Help workers Know their Rights</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br><br>New York, NY 10019</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hands Off NYC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Keep showing up in solidarity with our neighbors. This day of business outreach will work in western midtown, where we&apos;ve had really good experiences helping department store managers, bar/restaurants, parking lots, etc to prepare and better protect employees in the event of ICE raids.

Join volunteers with Target Majority NYC (an Indivisible and Swing Left group) to talk to business owners and managers and teach them the crucial Know Your Rights info they need to better protect their employees in the event of an ICE Raid. You&apos;ll help them put up signs to declare their solidarity, and to create as much protection as possible within their place of work.

We will provide training on the spot, but you can also start prepping now by visiting https://tinyurl.com/startSOS

**A core principle behind all Target Majority NYC events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values. We recommend all participants review [Indivisible&apos;s safety and security resources](https://indivisi.org/safety) before this event**</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/896540/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
