        <name>UWS ICE Readiness Workshop</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>UWS ICE Readiness Workshop</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Upper West Side<br><br>New York, NY 10024</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hands Off NYC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Minnesota has shown us that building up a strong community connection is the best way to protect our neighbors against ICE. That&apos;s why this community weekend, neighbors from the UWS are planning a Town Hall that is one part education, one part connection and discussion, and one part action.  

The day will help people learn not only how to spot ICE and what to do when that happens, but also how to strengthen our community through mutual aid, neighborhood gatherings, and walking groups.  Equal parts presentation, discussion, and action, we aim for everyone to leave knowing more of their neighbors and feeling empowered to build together.

Please dress warmly as we will end the event with an activity.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/897755/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
