        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Hands Off NYC Neighborhood Action: Whistle and Know Your Rights Distribution in Manhattan Valley</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>221 W 107th St<br>New York, NY 10025</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hands Off NYC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>As part of the Handsoffnyc&apos;s effort to defend our neighborhoods from ICE Upper West Side Action Group is organizing volunteers to distribute whistles along with flyers of how to use them to defend if ICE comes, know your rights and reporting ICE to people in the street in Manhattan Valley. We&apos;ll meet in the Durar Cafe restaurant for a training and to get materials and a location assigned, pair off and then set out to talk to people on the street. We&apos;ll return to the restaurant around 2:30-2:45pm when we&apos;re finished to debrief together.</p>
