        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Neighbors United for Immigrant Safety Workplace Outreach</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Harlem (exact location varies by day)<br><br>New York, NY 10027</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Harlem</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join our Harlem/UWS outreach effort to help local businesses and workers prepare to respond to ICE raids. 

Spanish very useful especially in East Harlem and West Harlem, but all help appreciated!

Working in pairs, we&apos;ll meet with owners, managers, and employees at their work sites to help them learn what to do now to protect themselves, what to do if ICE comes, what to do in case of detentions, and where to find additional resources. We&apos;ll supply multilingual materials for employers and employees, and scripts for volunteers.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/838849/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
