<h3>We Are The Future. ICE Is Not. A March for Immigrant Justice.</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Red Bank<br>Monmouth St<br>Red Bank, NJ 07701</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> AFSC New Jersey Immigrant Rights</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for a youth-led community gathering uplifting immigrant voices and calling for dignity, safety, and justice for our immigrant community. This march centers young people organizing in solidarity with immigrant communities and standing against harmful detention and enforcement practices carried out by U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement. Everyone is welcome to attend. 

AFSC NJ will be launching an emergency cash assistance fund to support families affected by detention and deportation - in addition to rapid responses who are observing ICE&apos;s actions.

Date: Saturday, February 28
Location: Red Bank Train Station
