        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>CD17 Immigration Democratic Party Congressional Candidate Forum</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Christ Episcopal Church<br>43 S Broadway<br>Tarrytown, NY 10591</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for a CD17 congressional candidate forum for voters that aims to promote an informed and respectful exchange focused on U.S. immigration policy in the midst of a national detention and deportation crisis. Democratic Party voters will hear congressional candidates national policy positions and specific approach to district issues which include: the proposed detention center in Chester, NY, 20 miles from the Rockland County district border; the documented criminal arrests by ICE without a judicial warrant in the district; and, the 287 municipal and county police agreements in with ICE in New York State. 

Questions: CD17 Voters: Please submit questions here: https://forms.gle/GpcFUXcN2iByqiEP7

Parking:
Municipal lot:
25 South Broadway, Tarrytown, NY 10591
https://maps.app.goo.gl/YG3HxMcotF2WQAPT8

Free parking lot at Washington Irving Intermediate School
34 Franklin, Tarrytown, NY 10591
https://maps.app.goo.gl/oDuXojfFtwF5xhXX8

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
