    <Placemark>
        <name>CITIZENS BANK: STOP FINANCING ICE PRISONS!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>CITIZENS BANK: STOP FINANCING ICE PRISONS!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 3:30 PM UTC - 4:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Sidewalks along Upper Glen Street in front of Citizens Bank and Queensbury Plaza<br>756 Upper Glen St<br>Queensbury, NY 12804</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible ADK/Saratoga</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Citizens Bank publicly presents itself as a community-centered institution committed to social responsibility, yet the bank continues to maintain key financial relationships with CoreCivic and The GEO Group: two notorious, for-profit, prison corporations that support ICE.  

In response, a coalition of progressive organizations has been holding peaceful, coordinated standouts near regional Citizens Bank branches. Our event will be a **Honk-n-Wave**. 🚗👋🏻 Learn more about this movement and view sign examples [in this Substack article.](https://grassrootsconnector.substack.com/p/crawl-walk-run)

**We plan to be out in solidarity with activists across the Northeast who won’t let weather deter them! **Sign Up or check this Mobilize page to be notified of any changes to the event.

**For this action, please keep your signs focused on these messages and use 4-5&quot; high letters for maximum visibility:**
📢Cages Aren’t Communities  
📢De-ICE Citizens Bank  
📢Citizens Bank: Invest in Communities, Not Cages  
📢End Mass Incarceration  
📢Say NO to CoreCivic and The GEO Group  
📢No Banks for Cages  
📢People Over Prison Profits  

**Join *We Rise Saturday* immediately following this event** to bring signs with your other powerful messages. (This is a weekly vigil held from 12-1pm at the Civil War Monument in Glens Falls, just a couple miles down the road.)  

🚗**Parking:** please park in the north end of the Queensbury Plaza shopping center parking lot (corner of Quaker Rd &amp; Route 9/Upper Glen St) *away from the businesses*.  

*A core principle behind all the DE-ICE Citizens Bank events is a **commitment to nonviolent action**. We expect all participants to seek to **de-escalate** any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events. **Please do not block the bus stop or pedestrian/vehicular traffic.***

&gt; Learn more about Citizens Bank’s relationship to the private prison system:  

&gt; CoreCivic and The GEO Group build and operate immigration detention facilities for ICE, provide transportation services to ICE, and operate prisons for mass incarceration. Go to boycottcitizens.org or contact the De-ICE Coalition at de.ICE.CitizensBank@gmail.com.  

&gt; The coalition calls upon Citizens Bank to live up to its stated values by publicly committing to end its financial relationships with private prison and detention contractors as soon as legally possible. These actions are intended to send a clear message: corporations and financial institutions that enable harmful immigration and detention policies must be held accountable by the communities they claim to serve.  


### This event is being co-sponsored by:

**Blue Line Indivisible** -- a local chapter of [Indivisible](http://Indivisible.org), active in northern Warren and southern Essex counties. *We are an inclusive, issue-driven group dedicated to creating positive change through positive action. We believe every person in the United States deserves equal rights and opportunities, regardless of race, gender, sexual orientation, immigration status, economic standing, religion, or disability. Our commitment is to a free and fair democracy—of the people, by the people, and for the people.*  

Find us online:   

[Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/groups/bluelineindivisible/?ref=share&amp;mibextid=NSMWBT)  

Email us: blue.line.indivisible@gmail.com  


### and  


**Indivisible ADK/Saratoga** -- a local chapter of [Indivisible](http://Indivisible.org), active in NY&apos;s Saratoga, Warren, and Washington counties, that welcomes people with our shared values and goals. *We organize and mobilize for actions that safeguard and advocate for vulnerable communities, protect human rights, guard our planet, elect progressive candidates and protect democracy. We are committed to non-violence as a guiding principle in everything we do.*   

Find us online:

[Website](https://www.indivisibleadksaratoga.com)

[Bluesky](https://bsky.app/profile/indivisible-adk.bsky.social)

[Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/share/g/19myt9wGmE)

[Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/indivisibleadksaratoga/)

Email us: indivisibleadksaratoga@gmail.com</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/901276/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
