        <name>Hands Off NYC Families Forest Hills</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Hands Off NYC Families Forest Hills</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>First Presbyterian Church of Forest Hills<br>70-35 112th St<br>Queens, NY 11375</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Hands Off NYC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Come by to strengthen connections with neighbors and get resources for helping to protect NYC families. This is a kid-friendly event, so bring the whole family! There will be activities for the kids, including an opportunity to write letters or draw pictures for children currently in ICE detention, a toy swap (bring a gently used toy and go home with one that’s “new” to you), and story time! We will also be collecting items for our food pantry, so please come with any unexpired, shelf stable pantry items you’d like to donate! We will also be taking (gently used and laundered, please!) clothing donations for adults and children, coats a plus!. 

Come by and get plugged in to all the ways we can show up for each other and all of our neighbors, and collectively imagine communities grounded in dignity and care.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/902131/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
