        <name>ICE Out for Good: Rally to De-Ice Nassau County!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out for Good: Rally to De-Ice Nassau County!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Northern Blvd side of Macy&apos;s Parking lot  (SouthEAST corner)<br>1100 Northern Blvd<br>Manhasset, NY 11030</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We are facing a crisis and we need all Members of Congress to fight back. Join your friends and neighbors in telling our representatives that we demand they use every tool at their disposal to refuse to fund ICE and Border Patrol without serious reforms. We cannot allow business as usual to fund brutality.

Join the Great Neck Democratic Club, the Manhasset Democratic Club, and the AHNEW Democratic Club (Albertson/Herricks/New Hyde Park/East Williston/Williston Park) and the Port Washington Democratic Club as we gather together and line up along Northern Blvd. to show support for RIDDING NASSAU COUNTY OF ITS RELATIONSHIP WITH ICE!

We will rally on the southwest corner of 25A (Northern Blvd) and Community Drive, in front of the Macy&apos;s parking lot on Northern Blvd.  PARK IN THE MACY&apos;S LOT.

PLEASE NOTE: A second rally is being held at the same time in front of Whole Foods, on Northern Blvd at the corner of Port Washington Blvd.  There is a separate event link for that rally.

*A core principle behind all ICE Out For Good events is a commitment to nonviolent action and no civil disobedience. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values, and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.</p>
