        <name>February Savannah Indivisible meeting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>February Savannah Indivisible meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Coastal Georgia Center<br>305 Fahm St<br>Savannah, GA 31401</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Savannah Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Those at our January meeting saw we were bursting at the seams, so we are moving Savannah Indivisible’s February group meeting and social to the Coastal Georgia Center. 

Our guest speaker will be Robert, a community organizer and activist in Minneapolis. He will share his firsthand experience caring for his neighbors in the face of state-sanctioned violence and how their leaderless network fights to stay one step ahead of ICE.

We will also break into teams to organize against the Trump regime and provide a network of mutual support. We will walk out with clear direction and actions for mobilization.

Finally, we’ll celebrate Savannah Indivisible’s first year in action with a potluck and celebratory cake. Feel free to bring a dish if you’d like to share, but no pressure. Come for the community and fellowship.

For this meeting’s mutual aid, we’re collecting personal hygiene products for Parker’s House Women’s Shelter. Here is a list of [recommended items](https://savannahindivisible.org/events/february-2026-group-meeting#:~:text=Personal%20Hygiene%20Products,Tampons%20and%20pads).

Whether you’re new or have been with us from the beginning, your presence matters. Bring your ideas. Bring your open mind. Bring your will to win. It will take all of us.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/888855/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
