<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>JOIN US to protest against the I.C.E. rampage across U.S. towns and cities!

We’ll have one or two large banners for motorists who drive through this busy intersection at the only stoplight in our region -- help us hold these banners! Please also bring your signs and U.S. flags. The theme is ICE brutality.

We are doing this honk &apos;n&apos; wave EVERY SATURDAY through March 7, maybe longer. ALL HANDS ON DECK for this important peaceful protest.

&quot;Freedom of speech is a principle that supports the freedom of an individual or a community to articulate their opinions and ideas without fear of retaliation, censorship, or legal sanction.&quot; ... One way of helping to ensure we keep our freedom of speech is by exercising it ... regularly.

These Bradford rallies are organized by Corinth/Topsham Indivisible and Third Act Orange East.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
