        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Know Your Rights Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 25, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Holderness Free Library<br>866 US-3<br>Holderness, NH 03245</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Central New Hampshire Indivisble</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Central NH Indivisible and ACLU-NH for a Know Your Rights Training at the Holderness Free Library on February 25th at 5:30pm. 

This event is limited to 50-participants, so sign up early.

Learn about your rights when encountering local law enforcement and federal immigration enforcement, while also learning best practices to document and report ICE activity. Knowing our rights, whether it is when we are encountering law enforcement or protesting, is imperative in ensuring those rights are upheld for everyone.

This training will be potluck-style! Please bring food to share if you are able.</p>
