        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>South County Rising OVERPASS BRIGADE - Exeter RI</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>130 Austin Farm Rd<br>Exeter, RI 02822</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> South County Rising RI</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This is a SOUTH COUNTY RISING event!

Saturday, February 28, we remember Renee Nicole Good &amp; Alex Pretti and all the victims of ICE and the Trump Regime.  Stand With Us while we demand an end to ICE cruelty in our country!

South County Rising protesters will gather at Austin Farm Rd in Exeter at the Rt 95 overpass.  

***Setup is at 11AM &amp; the brigade will run from 11:30AM to 12:30PM.***

There&apos;s plenty of parking on both sides of the Road. 
We will provide letters to hold and large flags.

To get there:  Put 130 Austin Farm Road Exeter in your GPS.  

From Hope Valley, head north on Rt. 3 (Nooseneck Hill Rd.) for about 7 miles. Austin Farm Road is a left turn after RT 165 intersection - before you get to Victory Highway, Rt. 102. The overpass is not far from the turn on Austin Farm Road. 

From the North on 95South, take Exit 14A toward NK/Exeter to Rt. 3 South.  Turn Right onto Rt 3 South and Austin Farm Road is the first right after the light.

A core principle behind all South County Rising events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.</p>
