<h3>Citizens Bank Protest</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Citizens<br>51 Main St<br>South Kingstown, RI 02879</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Rhode Island</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Are you horrified by ICE?

Join South County Resistance on Saturday, March 7th, 2026 from 11am -12pm as we stand outside Citizens Bank branches at 41 Main Street in Wakefield, RI or at 10 Woodruff Ave in Narragansett to demand that they stop financing ICE. Please join us at either location!

Feel free to bring signs. Dress warmly.

Notorious private prison companies The GEO Group and CoreCivic are being called on to be part of an unprecedented expansion in capacity as part of the Trump administration’s mass detention, deportation, and surveillance policies.

Citizens Bank says it’s strengthening communities, but has continued financing CoreCivic and GEO Group as other lenders have cut ties. Private prisons and the mass detention, deportation, and surveillance of immigrants don’t strengthen our communities; they hurt our neighbors. Citizens must stop financing CoreCivic and GEO Group.

A core principle behind all our events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.</p>
