    <Placemark>
        <name>**Wed, Feb 18th** following National Day of Lobbying: Impeach Trump/Defund ICE - Metaririe (LA-01)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>**Wed, Feb 18th** following National Day of Lobbying: Impeach Trump/Defund ICE - Metaririe (LA-01)</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Rep Scalise&apos;s Metairie office<br>111 Veterans Memorial Blvd suite 803<br>Metairie, LA 70005</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> 50501Missouri</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**WEDNESDAY, FEB 18** 

We will meet with Rep Scalise&apos;s office the day AFTER 2.17 (as 2.17 is Mardi Gras).

In the first week of 2026, the administration engaged in three flagrant abuses of power: (1) an unconstitutional military strike in Venezuela, (2) the extrajudicial murder of Renee Nicole Good by a member of the ICE paramilitary force for exercising her first amendment rights, and (3) the continued obstruction of justice for victims of Jeffrey Epstein’s child sex trafficking ring. A month into 2026, the administration has escalated their unchecked aggression against allies like Greenland and countries like Cuba, Columbia, and Mexico. ICE has kidnapped preschoolers and used them as bait for their parents, and the administration is considering deploying military police to back them up.

In short: It’s not getting better and Congress is not meeting the moment. 

Democracy does not defend itself; it requires the active participation of the people. While countless Americans have already called, emailed, written letters, signed petitions, and while activist organizations have brought groups to Capitol Hill calling for impeachment, this moment demands something more visible, more direct, and more powerful: constituents showing up at congressional district offices, where staff rarely, if ever, engage with constituents.

Impeachment is not optional. It is the remedy mandated by the Constitution. Likewise, Congress holds the power to de-fund and abolish ICE. They aren’t acting because they do not have the political will to do so. So we will lend them some of ours.

WHO/WHEN:

FLARE USA, Citizens&apos; Impeachment, and 50501 Movement are proud to announce the next National Day of Action: in-district lobbying on February 17, 2026 for the impeachment of President Trump and the complete abolishment of ICE. Representatives will be in their districts; it&apos;s time to catch them at home. It&apos;s time to Remove the Regime AND abolish ICE!

Grassroots pro-democracy organizations (e.g., local chapters of Indivisible, Hands Off, 50501), progressive primary candidates, and other concerned citizens will join together in leading constituents into the local/in-district offices of all 435 US House Representatives to demand impeachment and the abolishment of ICE. 

Please see our attendee guide for more information on why we&apos;re mobilizing, specific goals, current news on impeachment, and a full guide, including scripts, for visiting and following up with your Representative&apos;s office at tinyurl.com/lobby217guide. 

By registering for the event, you are agreeing that event partners may receive your contact information and communicate with you about related activities. 

All participants are committed to lawful, non-violent action and no civil disobedience.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903848/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
