        <name>CITIZENS BANK: STOP FUNDING ICE PRISONS!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>CITIZENS BANK: STOP FUNDING ICE PRISONS!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Public Sidewalks Near<br>120 Waterman St<br>Providence, RI 02906</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> DE-ICE Citizens Bank Rhode Island</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Citizens Bank publicly presents itself as a community-centered institution committed to social responsibility. Yet the bank continues to maintain key financial relationships with CoreCivic and The GEO Group: two notorious, for-profit, prison corporations that build and operate immigration detention facilities for ICE, provide transportation services to ICE, and operate prisons for mass incarceration. For more information about Citizens Bank’s relationship to the private prison system, go to boycottcitizens.org or contact the De-ICE Coalition at de.ICE.CitizensBank@gmail.com.

In response, a coalition of progressive organizations from Massachusetts, Rhode Island, and beyond will hold peaceful, coordinated standouts near regional Citizens Bank branches on Saturday, March 7, 2026. 

An interactive map of participating locations is available here:  
https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1AqRhnn9dpUufZYdnkwFm6cDhqDWM6Tc&amp;ll=42.47280688951886%2C-71.8565222&amp;z=9

Rhode Island Standouts are taking place at the following branch locations on March 7 from 11:00am to Noon:

East Side - 120 Waterman St 02906 https://mobilize.us/s/V8G9Py

Narragansett - 10 Woodruff Ave 02882

Wakefield - 51 Main St 02879

Westerly - 112 Franklin St 02891

You can take action now! Go to BoycottCitizens.org to learn more.

On March 7th, dress warm, bring your voice and your favorite sign to tell Citizens Bank that their mission is to support community not cage it!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904325/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
