    <Placemark>
        <name>Target and Home Depot De-Shopping Demonstrations</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Target and Home Depot De-Shopping Demonstrations</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br><br>Lowell, MA 01852</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>ICE OUT! JOIN US FOR A DE-SHOPPING DEMONSTRATION. 

📍 Feb 26 – 10 AM - Home Depot 85 Main St Tewksbury
📍 Feb 28 – 10 AM- Target 181 Plain St Lowell

For decades, Home Depot has profited from immigrant labor—now its silence enables ICE raids that terrorize workers and communities. Target has also allowed ICE activity while backing policies that harm immigrants. They are both supporting this regime of domestic terrorists. 

We demand that Home Depot and Target:

Publicly condemn ICE raids

Stop cooperating with ICE

Protect workers and customers

Refuse access to private spaces without a judicial warrant

Stand with our communities, not support the terror against them

Corporations cannot profit from our communities while allowing them to be attacked.

At Home Depot, we will load our carriages with ICE Scrapers and / or de-icer, and purchase them (until they sell out). Then we will all get in the customer service line to return them. 

At Target, we will load our carriages with a container of Salt, and purchase it. Then we will all get in the customer service line to return them.

IMPORTANT- BRING CASH!! No need for them to have our info to tattle to ICE, and it takes longer for a cash purchase and return. 

✊ Nonviolent action. Community defense. ICE OUT. Join us.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
