        <name>ICE OUT FOR GOOD</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT FOR GOOD</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 8:30 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Lower Square<br>Central Avenue &amp; Washington Street<br>Dover, NH 03820</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Greater Seacoast NH Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Bring your signs, yourselves and your friends, and let&apos;s take a stand for freedom, the law, and the Constitution! Not a penny more to fund ICE&apos;s brutality and terror machine, and its unconstitutional seizure and imprisonment of US residents. No kidnapping human beings and warehousing them as if they were Amazon packages!  

Our senators and our congressman need to see that we oppose any further funding to the already bloated ICE budget.

Parking:  On the street, behind the Dover Public Library (73 Locust St), or in the Orchard St parking garage (45 Orchard St).</p>
