        <name>Know Your Rights as an Ally of Immigrants Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Know Your Rights as an Ally of Immigrants Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>United Methodist Church of Evergreen<br>3757 Ponderosa Dr<br>Evergreen, CO 80439</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Foothills Democracy Defenders</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for Know Your Rights as an Ally training, presented by the Denver Justice Project. This training is for allies and observers who want to support immigrant communities during ICE and immigration enforcement encounters. 

You will learn:
- The rights of immigrants during ICE interactions
- The role, rights and limits of allies and observers
- How to safely observe and document enforcement

This training is immigration-specific; Not a general Know Your Rights workshop. 

There is NO fee, but donations will be accepted to support Denver Justice Project&apos;s important work. Learn more about Denver Justice here: https://www.denverjusticeproject.org/</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/898798/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
