        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT NOW! A report from the frontlines.</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 11:30 PM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Dunedin Scottish Center<br>917 Louden Ave<br>Dunedin, FL 34698</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Pinellas County Democrats</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>From heartwarming to heartbreaking stories - personal perspectives and insights from the anti-ICE protests in Minnesota by Rev. Mike MacMillan, Faith United Church of Christ, Dunedin.

We will also have Leela Gray, Earle Forde, and Brandt Robinson, Congressional candidates for D13 to speak about their platforms.  All speakers will have time for Q &amp; A after their own talks.

The North Pinellas County Democratic Club meeting starts with social time at 6:30 pm, followed by the business meeting at 7:00 pm. Attendees may purchase from the Center&apos;s cash bar&apos;s snacks, beer and wine. We’ll provide a Zoom link in an email to members a few days before the meeting for those who wish to join virtually.</p>
