        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Solidarity with Detained Immigrants</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>14450 49th Street N<br>Clearwater, FL 33762</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>In cooperation with The Interfaith Alliance, we are hosting a weekly vigil/demonstration on 49th street by the Pinellas Courthouse Complex.

At least 30 people died in ICE “Detention” in 2025. Currently more than 59,000 immigrants are being held by ICE, separated from friends, family, and enduring inhumane conditions. Our government via ICE is perpetrating human right violations. We will not stand by while watching it happen. Please join us for this weekly action, in solidarity with the mothers, fathers, sons and daughters being held by ICE. We will not stop til the detention centers are closed and our immigrant friends are given due process and released.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
