        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Students Rise Up: Protest Training + Sign-Making Workshop</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 23, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 11:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>FAU College of Education, Room 124<br><br>Boca Raton, FL 33431</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Youth Action Fund</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>FAU PD has partnered with ICE in the 287(g) program. This allows FAU PD to conduct immigration enforcement during routine police duty, including **&quot;the power and authority to arrest without a warrant.&quot;** This assault on due process and human dignity exposes **all** 31,000+ students at FAU across six campuses to harassment, detention, abduction, and deportation.

Join us in College of Education room 124 for a workshop covering the plans for the school walkout on February 25th, your protest rights, and to design protest signs with us. Feel free to bring your own supplies, but some will be provided.

*(!) Non-FAU participants may attend, but you will not find free parking on campus. Parking is $2/hour at Garage 1 on Volusia St. just west of the library.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/906223/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
