        <name>F.A.F.O March - Forever Against Fascist Oppression March - Indivisible Wilton Manors</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>F.A.F.O March - Forever Against Fascist Oppression March - Indivisible Wilton Manors</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Corner of US1 &amp; E Commercial Blvd<br>5000 N Federal Hwy<br>Fort Lauderdale, FL 33308</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This is a local Indivisible Wilton Manors event.

**The F.A.F.O March, Forever Against Fascist Oppression March.**

Join us as we march **from Fort Lauderdale**, over the bridge, in **to Lauderdale By The Sea (LBTS)**, to protest there against this administration and their current actions in our country against it&apos;s own people.
**We the people *RESIST &amp; REJECT* all forms of authoritarian and fascist regimes!**
Stand with us, march with us, walk with us. EVERYONE is needed! Join us wherever you can join us from, if the walk is too long meet us enroute.

*Why Lauderdale By The Sea?*
Because they have sided with the corrupt, wannabe dictator, and are renaming a street after him! They do not care about anyone in our community and have demonstrated this by allowing their elected officials to dictate that the street will be renamed after the convicted Felon. Even after We The People stood up, spoke out and voted in majority against the renaming of one of **OUR STREETS** after a sexual abuser and friend of abusers.
We do **NOT** support nor enable this administration nor their violent terroristic government funded ICE agents nor their delusional, weak, cowardly leader. We do not support business&apos; that support them either!
While not all of LBTS stands by this attack on our community, our families, our friends, our loved ones, **MANY DO!!!!**
**WE RESIST! WE SAY NO TO ALL FORMS OF OPPRESSION!**
**We are WE THE PEOPLE and WE SAY FUCK ALL FASCISTS!**
**F.A.F.O FOREVER AGAINST FASCIST OPPRESSION!**

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/890021/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
