        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Solidarity in Community Aid</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 1:30 AM UTC - 3:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Salt Lake City Public Library<br>210 E 400 S<br>Salt Lake City, UT 84111</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>As ICE tears up our communities, and anti- diversity, equity and inclusion laws harm our marginalized communities, we must stand in solidarity in many ways. We protest, we rally, we write and call our elected officials. These actions are powerful, but the harm done to our neighbors is not relieved.

Solidarity in Community Aid is our community coming together to support students in crisis. Join us Wednesday, February 18th at 6:30 p.m. at the Salt Lake City Library to learn how community aid can help affected students.

Without recourse to institutional support as once provided by dedicated diversity, equity and inclusion initiatives, our community stands ready to lend support wherever needed. Join us to be a part of the solution rather than an onlooker to the crisis unfolding before us.

Speakers will be Dr. Ana Antunes, Juliet Reyonalds, State Senator Nate Blouin, and student Bhavika Malik. This will be in-person only, so please sign up here.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
