        <name>Pinal County Board of Supervisors&apos; Meeting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Pinal County Board of Supervisors&apos; Meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 4:30 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Board of Supervisors Hearing Room<br>135 N Pinal St<br>Florence, AZ 85132</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Queen Creek San Tan Valley Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Pinal County has referred County Attorney Brad Miller to AZ AG Kris Mayes for investigation regarding his contract with ICE signed in August and tearing through the peace on our streets until January 7th.  Today (February 9), ICE has been active on the streets of Pinal County again.  PCSO has been out in force, and ICE has been reported.  It is unclear if PCSO is directly working with ICE, which is a problem given the report from the BOS meeting in January.  We will update this invitation as we learn more.  

We sent a thank-you note to the BOS for their referral of Brad Miller to the AG&apos;s office.  They have also taken time to speak with us and hear our concerns and we appreciate that.  We have signs saying &quot;Thank you&quot; and others that can be held up by those attending the meeting.  

We want to support the BOS when they are making choices to protect taxpayer monies, our neighbors, and our families.  Please come to the BOS meeting to help us show solidarity for our neighbors who are vulnerable when ICE comes into our communities.  Brad Miller expressed that he disagrees with the BOS, and we need to step up and be as proactive as we can!

[Click here to find the agenda when it becomes available](https://www.pinal.gov/Calendar.aspx?EID=3224)

Observations between September and January 7th:

The Task Force Model is the one we began seeing on our streets beginning in August. This model seemed to use PCSO to pull over people of color, take their time to give a ticket while they waited for ICE, then monitor the situation, assist, and protect ICE during the abduction. We have not seen this type of law enforcement stop since the county began consulting attorneys on the matter. With ICE descending upon our state as I type, we do not want Brad Miller to unleash the Task Force Model on our neighborhoods again. During the time he was illegally cooperating with ICE from August through January, I personally saw 3 stops in and near my neighborhood. They were agressive and one of the people detained was an American.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/900038/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
