        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>AZ-01 Action: ICE OUTside of Schweikert&apos;s Office</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 23, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 4:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>David Schweikert&apos;s Office<br>14500 N Northsight Blvd<br>Scottsdale, AZ 85260</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> MoveOn</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The deaths of Alex Pretti and Renee Good have shaken communities across the country and raised serious concerns about accountability, public safety, and the impact of federal immigration enforcement. People are speaking out against what they view as unchecked violence and lawlessness within ICE and CBP operations and neighbors are coming together to call for transparency, real safety, and care, not fear.

Across the nation, people are taking action against what they see as harmful enforcement practices and demanding that Congress: Vote NO on any new funding for ICE or CBP, End ICE and Border Patrol operations in our communities, especially in sensitive locations like places of worship, schools, and hospitals, and Stop warrantless arrests and enforcement based on racial profiling. 

We are outraged by the actions of ICE and Border Patrol. We demand real accountability and that Congress reject funding increases in the DHS appropriations bill and legislate restrictions and reformations on ICE and Border Patrol.

Join us for a peaceful Community Honk &amp; Wave. We will also send a delegation up to Rep. Schweikert&apos;s Office to share our one-pager with him and tell him that we stand together and call for Congress to take that money and invest it where it belongs: in health care, social services, and real public safety.

Additionally, please bring non-perishable food and personal care items to be donated to the South Scottsdale Food Bank. We are currently also accepting excess citrus! To date our protests have donated more than 3 tons of food.

This event is being presented by a coalition of local groups including Indivisible, Swing Left, Honest Arizona, and MoveOn.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903432/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
