    <Placemark>
        <name>Join Mesa Valley Indivisible to Protest ICE Deportations &amp; the AROCC Detention Center</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Join Mesa Valley Indivisible to Protest ICE Deportations &amp; the AROCC Detention Center</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>South Gilbert Road &amp; East Broadway Road<br>Mesa, AZ 85204</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Mesa Valley Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## 🛫 ICE &amp; AROCC: Stop ICE operations at Mesa Gateway Airport!

For the past eight months, [Mesa Valley Indivisible](https://www.mesavalleyindivisible.org/) members and a coalition of groups around the country have been working relentlessly to end Avelo Airlines’ involvement in the unlawful and inhumane deportation of primarily non‑violent immigrants via Mesa Gateway Airport. 

Americans dedicated to ending Avelo&apos;s contract with ICE boycotted, protested, emailed and called our representatives/senators, held weekly meetings, etc. and on January 7, 2026, news broke that Avelo Airlines announced they were ending their ICE deportation flights!!

As we all celebrate this **HUGE WIN**, we also know ICE deportation flights are still occurring at the Mesa Gateway Airport &amp; the AROCC detention center remains active on the grounds. We can happily check off Avelo Airlines now, but it is time to move on to the next challenge which is ending ICE deportation flights &amp; closing the AROCC at our Mesa Gateway Airport! 

## 📢Join us on Saturday, February 21st, to challenge the use of the local airport for what are illegal, inhumane, and unconstitutional removal operations.

### 🆘Key Concerns Driving the Protest:

- **Corporate Complicity in Inhumane Practices**: These deportations are driven by profit and political patronage. Private contractors run detention and flight operations through non‑commercial hubs, creating durable infrastructure that outlasts elections. The incentive loop is clear: **more arrests → more funding → more capacity → more bodies.**


- **Conditions on the Ground**: Individuals slated for deportation or transfer are held in a secluded facility at the Mesa airport—near where commercial travelers dine—where they are reportedly kept without access to basic amenities like beds or showers until their flight.


- **Inhumane Treatment on Flights**: Documentation over years has shown that passengers on these flights are typically shackled for the entire duration, denied bathroom access, and subjected to severe abuse, including beatings, restrictive restraints, and reports of deaths and miscarriages.


- **Secrecy and Lack of Transparency**: Aircraft are often disguised through subcontractors and subleases, and the flights themselves are secretive and unmarked, shielding the carriers and the airport from public scrutiny.


### 🪧Signs &amp; Graphics

Please create signs and graphics that are relevant to ICE deportations &amp; the AROCC! Some ideas include:

* Abolish ICE
* ICE separates families
*42 days does not = temporary
* Illegal deportations without due process is human trafficking


###  ⚠️Protest Information

🚗 Parking is available around the intersection 

⭐ Please share with friends, family, neighbors, EVERYONE!

📸 When posting photos/videos online, please make sure to tag the Mesa Valley Indivisible social media page and clearly state Mesa Valley Indivisible as the protest organizer. The goal is to raise our group&apos;s profile which will make it easier for new people to find &amp; join our community while also increasing our influence with government officials and the media! In order to have a greater impact on our city, people have to know we exist first!!

#mesavalleyindivisible #abolishice #closearocc #dueprocess #immigrants</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/865688/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
