        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT FOR GOOD - People Over Policies - Anthem Indivisible</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 8, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Carefree Highway Overpass<br>I-17 and Carefree Highway<br>Phoenix, AZ 85086</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Anthem Indivisible Arizona</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>### People Matter

Immigrants are and have been a key part of our community.  They are not taking the worst of the worst, they are taking valuable neighbors who have often been here for years, doing their part to make our economies, neighborhoods, and culture more vital.  No one deserves to be disappeared into these inhumane detention centers.

Join **Anthem Indivisible on Sunday, March 8, 2026, from 11:00 AM to 1:00 PM** as we gather on the **Carefree Highway overpass** to stand in solidarity with our immigrant neighbors and raise our collective voice against the abuses carried out by ICE.

This action is part of our ongoing ICE OUT FOR GOOD series — peaceful, visible, people powered demonstrations that affirm our shared values of dignity, safety, and human rights. When we show up together, we send a clear message: our neighbors deserve protection, not persecution.
We’ll hold signs, wave to passing cars, and stand shoulder to shoulder in nonviolent community action. Whether you’ve been with us since the first rally or this is your first time, your presence strengthens our collective voice.

#### Arrival &amp; Rally Details
Please plan to arrive by **10:45 AM at the Chili’s parking lot at 34710 N North Valley Parkway, Phoenix, AZ 85086.** We&apos;ll head up together to the overpass for a prompt **11:00 AM start.** There will be cars to bring you to and from the overpass if you don&apos;t want to make the walk. The rally wraps up at **1:00 PM.**

#### Pro Tips for a Comfortable Rally:

-	Bring a hat, wear sunscreen, and consider an umbrella for shade
-	A portable stool can be helpful if you prefer to sit while holding your sign
-	Hydrate! Bring water and whatever fuel you need to stay energized
-	Creative signs and expressive sunglasses strongly encouraged 

*A core principle behind all ICE Out For Good events is a commitment to nonviolent action and no civil disobedience. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values, and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events. All events should be held in public spaces or on public property.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904931/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
