<h3>Community Care Night: ICE Safety and Naloxone Kit Assembly</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>1540 E Cypress St suite 1<br>Phoenix, AZ 85006</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Fuerte Arts Movement</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for a hands-on community prep night!

We’ll be putting together whistle kits and cutting out Know Your Rights cards that will be distributed to community members. This is a simple but powerful way to support rapid response efforts and make sure our neighbors have important tools and information.

We will also be making Naloxone and safe use kits through partnerships with Sonoran Prevention Works, these are life saving kits that our community is in need of.  

No experience needed — just come ready to help, connect, and be in community.

All supplies will be provided.

What we’ll be doing:
• Assembling whistle kits
• Cutting and preparing Know Your Rights cards
• Building community and supporting preparedness efforts

Bring a friend and come hang out while doing meaningful work together.</p>
