        <name>Know What’s Coming: The Real Impact of ICE Detention</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Know What’s Coming: The Real Impact of ICE Detention</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>17540 Ave of the Arts<br>Surprise, AZ 85378</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Northwest Valley Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## Know What’s Coming: The Real Impact of ICE Detention  
**Thursday, February 19 • 6:00 PM • Surprise**

As city, state, and federal officials send letters to DHS asking for more information about the proposed ICE detention facility in Surprise, our community doesn’t have to wait to understand what detention brings.

Other communities in Arizona have already lived it.

Join Northwest Valley Indivisible for a timely presentation with Semillas Arizona examining how detention facilities operate, how they’re funded, what documented conditions exist inside, and how these facilities impact families, neighborhoods, schools, and local resources.

If an ICE facility comes to Surprise, it will shape our city — not just politically, but economically and culturally. This event will ground the conversation in facts and lived experience from across the state, and clarify what community members can realistically do at the local level.

While others are asking for answers, we’re bringing them.

If you care about what kind of city Surprise will be, join us.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/902337/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
