        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Freedom From ICE Friday</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 11:30 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>North Hamilton Street &amp; East Trent Avenue<br>Spokane, WA 99202</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Another American citizen was killed by Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) in Minneapolis, Minnesota. This killing is part of a broader pattern of unchecked violence, impunity, and abuse carried out by federal immigration enforcement agencies against members of our communities.

Join us in solidarity for Minnesota, and to demand accountability, honor the lives lost, and make visible the human cost of ICE’s actions.

A core principle behind all events is a commitment to nonviolent action and no civil disobedience. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values, and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.

Reminder for all our events we follow the PJALS Non-Violence Guidelines. https://pjals.org/action/#nonviolence

Closest Business is Global Thrift 919 E Trent Ave Spokane, WA 99202

Hang out afterwards at NoLi Northern Lights Brewing Co &amp; Pub 1003 E Trent Ave, Spokane, WA 99202

PLEASE BE MINDFUL ABOUT PARKING and park on the streets. Please do not park in the lot by NoLi, Barre, etc. until after the rally if you plan to hang out at NoLi. We don&apos;t want anyone to be towed. Thank you!</p>
