        <name>Handmaids of LV - Feb 22nd ICE: Release Our Children Rally &amp; March!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Handmaids of LV - Feb 22nd ICE: Release Our Children Rally &amp; March!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Las Vegas Federal Courthouse<br>333 S Las Vegas Blvd<br>Las Vegas, NV 89101</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Handmaids Las Vegas</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join the Handmaids of Las Vegas on February 22, 2026 at 12pm at the Las Vegas Federal Courthouse to take a stand against ICE and demand they RELEASE OUR CHILDREN. 

#ICEOutNow
#ReleaseOurChildren
#handmaidsoflv
#handmaidsoflasvegas
#HandmaidsInAction
#unity
#SolidarityInAction
#nevadaimmigration

A Stand for Dignity and Humanity Under the current Trump regime, immigrants and people of color have faced cruel and inhumane treatment. Families have been torn apart, children have been subjected to unjust policies that strip away their dignity and rights. We believe that every person deserves to be treated with respect and compassion, regardless of their background or origin.

How You Can Show Support Join Us: Wear red and stand with us in solidarity. Your presence will amplify our message and show that our community stands united.

Donate: Bring non-perishable food and clothing to help support our local community. Your contributions make a significant difference in the lives of those in need.

Together, We Rise This is not just a call to action; it is a call to the heart. By standing together, we send a powerful message that we will not remain silent in the face of injustice. Let us continue to stand until justice prevails, and every individual is treated with the respect they deserve.

Join us, bring your compassion, and be a part of a movement that believes in the power of unity and love. Together, we can create a brighter, more just future for all.

With hope and determination,

The Handmaids of Las Vegas</p>
