<h3>FEB 20th! - Handmaids of LV - ICE OUT NOW! Downtown Las Vegas 3pm</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>ICE OFFICE - Downtown Las Vegas<br>501 Las Vegas Blvd S<br>Las Vegas, NV 89101</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Handmaids Las Vegas</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join the Handmaids of Las Vegas: ICE Out for GOOD - We Stand With Minnesota!

Dear compassionate souls of Las Vegas,

Wednesday, January 7, 2026 an American citizen was killed by Immigration and Customs Enforcement )ICE) in Minneapolis, Minnesota and now another life, Alex Pretti, has been taken by ICE. These killings are part of a broader pattern of unchecked violence, impunity and abuse carried out by federal immigration enforcement agencies against members of our communities.

A broad coalition of groups across the country is calling for a coordinated solidarity actions to stand and say ICE OUT FOR GOOD! with Minnesota, and to demand accountability, honor the lives lost, and make visible the human cost of ICE&apos;s actions.

A core principle behind all ICE Out events is a commitment to nonviolent action and no civil disobedience. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values, and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events. All events should be held in public spaces or on public property. Handmaids of Las Vegas are managing data and communications with participants. By registering for this event, you agree to receive info from the Handmaids of Las Vegas about the event, receive communications via email and/or SMS messages, and receive any other updates and opportunities to take action or support ICE OUT STANDS AND PARCHES. You also agree to have any data entered in this registration collected by Handmaids of Las Vegas. We will treat your data according to our organizations privacy policy.

We invite you to join the Handmaids of Las Vegas as we unite in a powerful demonstration of solidarity for immigrant rights. On February 20, 2026, we will gather every other Friday at the ICE Offices in Downtown Las Vegas. Our stands will take place from 3pm PM to 4:30 PM, where we will stand together, clad in the iconic red uniforms of the handmaids, to echo the call for justice and equality.

A Stand for Dignity and Humanity Under the current Trump regime, immigrants and people of color have faced cruel and inhumane treatment. Families have been torn apart, and countless individuals have been subjected to unjust policies that strip away their dignity and rights. We believe that every person deserves to be treated with respect and compassion, regardless of their background or origin.

How You Can Show Support Join Us: Wear red and stand with us in solidarity. Your presence will amplify our message and show that our community stands united.

Donate: Bring non-perishable food and clothing to help support our local community. Your contributions make a significant difference in the lives of those in need.

Together, We Rise This is not just a call to action; it is a call to the heart. By standing together, we send a powerful message that we will not remain silent in the face of injustice. Let us continue to stand until justice prevails, and every individual is treated with the respect they deserve.

Join us, bring your compassion, and be a part of a movement that believes in the power of unity and love. Together, we can create a brighter, more just future for all.

With hope and determination,

The Handmaids of Las Vegas</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/902086/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
