        <name>Legal Observer Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Legal Observer Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 6, 2026 at 2:00 AM UTC - 4:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>UCC Church<br>205 N Maple St<br>Colville, WA 99114</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This a local Indivisible event!

Indivisible Colville is proud to partner with a local community organizer for a training presentation on acting as a legal observer in the presence of federal immigration enforcement. You’ll learn to identify and validate judicial warrants, understand the role and limits of observers, and gain practical knowledge to help protect the rights of our vulnerable community members and ensure everyone is afforded their right to due process.
Our guest speaker is a longtime activist and community organizer, an ACLU of Oregon legal observer, and a co-founder of Gorge ICE Resistance. She has first-hand, real-world experience and perspective as a legal observer.
March 5th 2026
6:00 PM
First Congregational UCC, 205 N Maple St, Colville

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
