        <name>ICE OUT OF ESCO/EPD CANCEL THE CONTRACT Wednesday Vigil</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT OF ESCO/EPD CANCEL THE CONTRACT Wednesday Vigil</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Escondido Police Department<br>1163 Centre City Parkway<br>Escondido, CA 92026</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible North County San Diego</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>WHERE:  Escondido Police Department 

WHAT:  Urge EPD and Escondido City Council to cancel the Agreement with DHS allowing ICE to use Escondido’s firing range.  

Please head to City Council (City Hall @ 5 pm) to voice your opposition or just be present.  Relevant materials posted after the Description. 

Signage should reflect: 

“NO EPD CONTRACT WITH ICE” 
“ICE OUT OF ESCONDIDO” 
“ICE MAKES EVERYONE LESS SAFE” 
____
- Link to all the contracts and agreements:  https://escondidoindivisible.org/links-to-documents-for-ice-use-of-firing-range/ 

- Send message to local lawmakers via Action Network:  https://buttondown.com/EscondidoIndivisible/archive/use-this-tool-kit-to-help-cancel-the-ice-contract/

- Schedule of Upcoming Events: Esco City Council meeting @ 5 pm (please fill out a yellow card up front and speak on *non-agenda item public comment*!) 

- Feb 25 - Rally at City Hall prior to City Council meeting (5 PM - Contract Review is ON the agenda for this meeting. Please attend and fill out yellow card up front to oppose contract &amp; you can also speak on Agenda Item #(xx - not published yet).

- Action Toolkit: https://docs.google.com/document/d/11bHBBRK43QUNw4geG99g7MrjqrjdKDfLZgayz-5X620/edit?tab=t.0</p>
