        <name>ICE Out of Home Depot: San Marcos</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out of Home Depot: San Marcos</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 6:30 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Home Depot<br>550 W San Marcos Blvd<br>San Marcos, CA 92069</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On the morning of February 28th, San Diegans will take part in a coordinated action at Home Depot stores across San Diego county. 

Participants will gather outside their local Home Depot for brief chants before entering the store calmly (no chanting inside). While carrying signs and engaging respectfully with customers and employees, each person will purchase a paint scraper at a staffed checkout line, then return it before exiting. A demand letter will be delivered to store management during the action. Each store will have a designated leader, and actions may vary slightly by location.

This is a collective, peaceful action to stand up for our neighbors and show the strength of community solidarity. Join us and make your voice count.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903089/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
