        <name>ICE Out of Home Depot - Mira Mesa</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out of Home Depot - Mira Mesa</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Home Depot Mira Mesa<br>10604 Westview Pkwy<br>San Diego, CA 92126</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Across the country, ICE agents continue to target immigrants in and around Home Depot stores — workers, customers, and surrounding communities. These raids are chaotic, violent, and sometimes deadly.

These atrocities are happening on Home Depot’s watch — on its properties, with its silence. The company has not taken public steps to resist or condemn these raids, nor has it demanded that the government stop carrying out enforcement operations at its stores. Through its silence and inaction, Home Depot has become ICE’s passive partner. Every raid on its properties deepens fear in our communities. 

On Saturday, February 28, join us in a county-wide protest to demand that Home Depot immediately:

PROTECT DAY LABORERS - Ensure the safety and dignity of workers seeking honest employment outside of Home Depot stores.

DENOUNCE THE RAIDS - Publicly oppose immigration enforcement raids that target our community.

KEEP HOME DEPOT PROPERTIES SAFE - Stop allowing Home Depot locations to be used for immigration enforcement activity. 

We will be presenting a letter of these demands to the Home Depot Mira Mesa manger to share with corporate leadership and protesting outside the store, kindly educating customers on Home Depot&apos;s complicity with ICE raids and harm to our communities. 

A core principle behind all events is a commitment to NONVIOLENT ACTION. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.</p>
