        <name>Feet on the Streets - with a twist- CV Eastlake area says Ice OUT of Home Depot!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Feet on the Streets - with a twist- CV Eastlake area says Ice OUT of Home Depot!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 8:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Eastlake CV Home Depot<br>1320 Eastlake Pkwy<br>Chula Vista, CA 91915</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

&quot;Saturday, February 28th, San Diegans will take part in a coordinated action at Home Depot stores across San Diego county. 

Participants will gather outside their local Home Depot for brief chants before entering the store calmly (no chanting inside). While carrying signs and engaging respectfully with customers and employees, each person will purchase a single small screw, with a credit card if you can (HD is charged fees for each transaction) at a staffed checkout line, then return it before exiting, telling the employee to tell Home Depot to &quot;SCREW ICE.&quot;    

A demand letter will be delivered to store management during the action. Each store will have a designated leader, and actions may vary slightly by location.

This is a collective, peaceful action to stand up for our neighbors and show the strength of community solidarity.

Join us and make your voice count.&quot;

Hi Everyone:

I just wanted to add that we will also be collecting pantry-stable items for the San Diego Food Bank

I&apos;ve been doing this simple, yet fun, effective Good Trouble for a couple of months now.  

I definitely am known at the H Street location  (I also leave a bunch of my mini protest notecards with a liberal rock at various spots throughout the store).   I wear a statement tee and pins -- you can&apos;t miss me, so the reactions as I&apos;m walking around (with my whistle on my arm) are usually positive, even from the employees.   So, have fun with it ... we are the face of &quot;Antifa,&quot; so I engage with everyone with a smile on my face!  Especially the employees, so be kind -- it&apos;s not the employees fault that their boss is greedy. 

Invite a friend to come with you -- let&apos;s make our voices heard throughout all of the San Diego HD locations!

See you on the streets! 
Janine</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/905187/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
