        <name>ICE Out Of Our Communities - San Diego Virtual Teach-in!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out Of Our Communities - San Diego Virtual Teach-in!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for an Ice Out Of Our Communities - virtual teach-in for our San Diego communities! 

Today, we are all witness to a crisis of human rights happening in our own cities, as Trump, Ice, and border patrol scapegoat our immigrant neighbors, and weaponize government.  But because people have mobilized and shown up- the tide is turning, and Ice has been exposed for what it is - a very real threat to our safety and civic life.  

Today, people across the U.S., and abroad, are chanting in unison:  ICE OUT OF OUR COMMUNITIES.   And we must know there is MUCH that we can do to get Ice OUT, and help turn the tide from hate to human rights.   

The TEACH-IN will cover:  What does it mean to get Ice OUT from the bottom up?   What can local and state officials do - right now - and how can i get started?  What policies can make a difference that we can lift up and push forward?  

This effort builds on years of organizing led by immigrant communities nationwide — from the fight against 287g contracts to the sanctuary victories that have proven local action works. Cities and states that say NO to ICE are a critical bulwark against mass deportations and the erosion of civil rights.

There is much that we can do locally.  And there is much that our elected officials can do — if we demand courage and leadership.  

Will you join us?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/901924/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
