        <name>Banner Drop in South San Clemente</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Banner Drop in South San Clemente</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 9:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Pedestrian Bridge<br>South El Camino Real &amp; Avenida San Dimas<br>San Clemente, CA 92672</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible SJC (CA)</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for our banner drop as we share our message with the thousands of people in cars as they pass by. It’s time to tell the world this is not okay and to encourage conversations. We already have the messages on large banners - No ICE, No Kings, Defend Democracy - but we need you. Bring yourself, some friends, a flag, and even a costume if you like. (For driver safety, please no protest posters, but if you have a suggestion for a banner topic let us know.) Come and enjoy the camaraderie of some wonderful people and our toe tapping music. 
We have a shared commitment to nonviolent peaceful actions. A peaceful presence is our strongest message and keeps everyone safe.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/899066/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
