        <name>Tell DHS We Stand With Our Neighbors</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Tell DHS We Stand With Our Neighbors</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 20, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Department of Homeland Security<br>12500 Tukwila International Blvd<br>Tukwila, WA 98168</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Southend Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join a group of pissed off but peaceful neighbors Thursday late afternoon / early evening to greet the agents and staff pulling out of the DHS parking lot with our signage, presence, and voices. They will be wrapping up their day of creating parent-less families, forcing school lock downs, deporting women and children to dangerous countries they&apos;ve never been, and terrorizing communities of color, all under the fascist Trump regime. 

We will be doing so lawfully and peacefully (but not quietly) on the public sidewalk outside of the Department of Homeland Security in Tukwila.

We will be reminding them of their sworn oath to the U.S. Constitution and to the American people, and NOT to the lawless, corrupt, court order-ignoring strongman currently soiling the White House. We will also make sure they know loud and clear that immigrants make our neighborhoods and communities better and stronger, and we will fight like hell to keep them here where they belong. 

No more abductions, no more murder, no more terror - ICE OUT NOW!

A core tenet of Indivisible is peaceful, non-violent resistance and we will abide by this at all actions we host or co-host.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/905191/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
