    <Placemark>
        <name>ICE OUT OF SAN DIEGO</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT OF SAN DIEGO</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 6:30 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>880 Front St<br>San Diego, CA 92101</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> San Diego &amp; Imperial Counties Labor Council, AFL-CIO</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Across the country, families are feeling the consequences of federal overreach. From attacks on due process and civil liberties to efforts to silence the free press and limit public access to information, these actions threaten the foundation of our democracy.

Everyday people are paying the price while those in power play political games with our rights and freedoms. These are not just policy choices; they are moral decisions that test who we are as a nation and whether we will stand up for justice, truth, and accountability.

Democracy dies in the dark. Now is the time to raise our voices, defend our rights, and demand transparency and fairness from those who claim to lead in our name.

Join us every Thursday outside the Federal Building (880 Front Street, San Diego) to demand that Washington fund care — not chaos. Together, we can send a clear message:

Gather at 10:30am and speaking program begins at 11:00am

• Healthcare is a human right.

• Food is a human right.

• San Diego stands for care, not chaos and cruelty.

This is more than a protest! It’s a stand for dignity, justice, and the right of every family to live free from fear. Bring your friends, your signs, and your voice. Together, we can show that San Diego stands for community, not cages. For more information contact us at cipriano.vargas@sdcounty.ca.gov</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/820439/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
