        <name>HONK &amp; WAVE PROTEST: ICE OUT FOR GOOD &amp; PRETTI</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>HONK &amp; WAVE PROTEST: ICE OUT FOR GOOD &amp; PRETTI</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Wood Village Center<br>NE 223rd Avenue &amp; NE Glisan Street<br>Wood Village, OR 97060</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Multnomah East Indivisible Group</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>HONK &amp; WAVE - ICE OUT FOR GOOD &amp; PRETTI

ALL SATURDAYS IN FEBRUARY:  7th, 14th, 21st, 28th.
THIS IS A 1 HOUR POP-UP PROTEST 10AM-11:00AM
RAIN OR SHINE - DRESS FOR THE WEATHER.

Join Multnomah East Indivisible (MEI) community members from Gresham, Wood Village, Troutdale, Fairview, Corbett!
We will meet at the Wood Village Shopping center.

Gather at the intersection of NE Glisan Street and NE 223rd on the NE Corner, protest along the public sidewalk.

This is a visibility protest not a rally or march. Bring your Signs!

We stand with Minnesotans and our fellow citizens across America.
Everyday we see and hear about those who are being kidnapped, beaten and kept in cages, moved far from their families. These citizens are denied due process that is guaranteed under our US laws. 
These folks are not criminals, they are people in our communities who are being denied basic human civil rights.

We have seen ICE &quot;Agents&quot; murder Good and Pretti and we have learned of the deaths of 38 other citizens at the hands of ICE.
 ICE &quot;agents&quot; operate within a broad pattern of unchecked violence, impunity, and abuse. This is unconstitutional, this is criminal and this is being carried out by federal immigration enforcement &quot;agents&quot; against members of our communities.  

We Stand with our Immigrant Families! Bring your signs, bring a friend, and meet fellow resistors. Stand up and Defend Democracy!  

Remind yourself of your rights as a protester here:

https://www.aclu.org/know-your-rights/protesters-rights

A core principle behind all ICE Out For Good events is a commitment to nonviolent action and no civil disobedience. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values, and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/895806/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
