        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Tuolumne County Indivisible General Meeting - February 26th</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 1:30 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Tuolumne County Library - Sonora<br>480 Greenley Rd<br>Sonora, CA 95370</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Tuolumne County Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**Join us for our February General Meeting of Tuolumne County Indivisible.**  
This is where we come together, meet new folks, see familiar faces, share updates, and move our work forward as a community.

The agenda is still coming together, but at this meeting we will:

- **Get an update on ICE Watch here in the foothills**  
- **Share updates on key elections and campaigns**, with opportunities to sign up to help  
- **Talk through next steps for local and regional organizing**  
- **Create space for connection and community**, including welcoming anyone who wants to bring their **red hat knitting project** to work on during the meeting with others.

Whether you’ve been here since the early days or you’re just finding your way to us, your voice matters and we want you in the room.
  
Come as you are. This is a friendly, collaborative space to listen, contribute, and stay connected.

We look forward to seeing you there. 💙</p>
