        <name>ICE out of Portland | Revoke the ICE Permit | Protest at City Hall</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE out of Portland | Revoke the ICE Permit | Protest at City Hall</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>1221 SW 4th Ave<br>Portland, OR 97204</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Portland Contra Las Deportaciones/Portland Against Deportations</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Rally at city hall to demand action from city councilors and the mayor take action to fight ICE!

Over 120 days passed since a land use violation was issued to the Portland ICE Facility to violating the human rights of detainees. In that time, the facility continued to operate as a detention center and homebase of operations for ICE to terrorize Portland. In that time the south waterfront was gassed and attacked with chemical weapons over and over, with no help from the city. No action has been taken to begin the reconsideration process to revoke the permit, despite these abuses.

This is completely unacceptable. City council members and the mayor continue to abdicate responsibility and act as though there is nothing they can do. They are hoping we don’t look into the city charter to see what powers they actually have.

Since the mayor and city council seem to be confused as to what power they have, we will be attending their meeting on 2/18 to inform them of the powers they have, and how we demand they use them. Join us!

This will be a rally outside of city hall at 5 pm on 2/18
We will then enter the chambers to present our demands to council at 5:45 pm.
Meet at 1221 SW 4th Ave, Portland OR</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903686/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
