<h3>NorCalResist- Know Your Rights</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 2:30 AM UTC - 4:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Placer County Health &amp; Human Services<br>11434 B Ave<br>Auburn, CA 95603</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Auburn CA</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Coffee Talk (Placer and Nevada Counties) is sponsoring a workshop by NorCal Resist for our community.  NorCal Resist provides many resources for the immigrant and refugee population in several northern California counties. Their organization hosts educational events and trainings, organize actions,, and maintain a variety of resources and programs that provide support for those in need.

Join them for this training  on Know Your Rights which includes:
1. Know your rights and how to assert them
2.How to navigate encounters with ICE/law enforcement
3. What to do if ICE comes to your door</p>
