        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Democracy Defense Weekly</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, February 22, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Intersection of Daniels Street and Milo Candini Drive<br>2360 Daniels St<br>Manteca, CA 95337</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Community Resistance Is Growing — Now in Manteca!

Join your neighbors and stand up for democracy, human rights, and our shared future.

Democracy Defense Weekly
📍 Intersection of Daniels Street &amp; Milo Candini Drive
      (Corner of Big League Dreams &amp; Behind Kohl’s)
🕒 Sundays 1:00pm – 2:00pm
✊ Stand-up or sit-in — all are welcome

We gather weekly to peacefully resist policies and actions that harm our communities and undermine democracy, including:
•	War and intervention in Venezuela driven by oil interests and cover-ups
•	DOJ manipulation and lack of transparency regarding the Epstein files
•	ICE abductions and deportations without due process
•	A do-nothing Congress that refuses to do its job
•	Gerrymandering aimed at silencing voters
•	A government that serves the wealthy instead of the People

Bring:
Signs • Flags • Drums • Lawn chairs (optional) • Your voice and your passion

Meet like-minded people who believe in justice, accountability, and people-powered democracy.

Even 15-minutes can make a difference.
Show up. Speak out. Be seen.

🕊 Our commitment:
All actions are peaceful and non-violent. Non-violence is essential to the strength, credibility, and success of our movement.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
