        <name>Save our Democracy/ICE OUT</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Save our Democracy/ICE OUT</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 7:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Vacaville City Hall<br>650 Merchant St<br>Vacaville, CA 95688</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Save our Democracy/ICE OUT
History is watching. Right now, our country faces critical challenges: ICE accountability, protecting voting rights from federal takeover through the SAVE Act, and defending the democratic principles we have taken for granted. Our country is in a constitutional crisis. It&apos;s time to take back our Democracy. We need to rise up and let our voices be heard.
Do this today: Invite three friends, call, text, email
Bring your creative signs and unstoppable spirit
Wear comfortable shoes and a camp chair if needed
Bring water, stay hydrated and a fully charge phone
The Golden rule: Keep it Peaceful. We are committed to non-violence.  Stay focused on the message. No stepping into the street or jay walking, the sidewalk is our stage. Our strength is in our unity and our values.
Do not engage with any agitators- don&apos;t take the bait!
Quick heads up - no public restrooms available, so plan accordingly.
History will ask: Where were you when democracy needed you most?
Let your answer be: I SHOWED UP.
Your presence and your voice matters!




*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
