        <name>In-person: Activist Action Lab in the Park</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>In-person: Activist Action Lab in the Park</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, April 25, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Eagle Park<br>650 Franklin St<br>Mountain View, CA 94041</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> It&apos;s Blue Turn</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us in the park for a **hands-on organizing fair** where you can meet our teams, try out different kinds of action, and find the role that fits you best This is for **everyone**, whether you’re brand-new and still figuring out “Where do I start?” or you’ve been volunteering for years and might be ready to try a new lane.

You’ll rotate through short, interactive stations hosted by different teams in our group: voter outreach, protest and visibility work, immigrant-justice /community action against ICE harassment, education and training, and more. At each stop you’ll **do** something small: a bite-sized practice activity or mini-training that gives you a feel for that kind of work.

 Our hope is that you leave having met new people, learned a few concrete skills, and found at least one team you’d like to plug into more deeply this year.  

Come as you are, bring a friend if you can, and experiment! See you in the park!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/900621/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
