        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Rowland Overpass Banner Drop</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 7:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Rowland Overpass Above Highway 101<br>101 Rowland Blvd<br>Novato, CA 94947</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Resist And Defend</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join with like-minded Marin residents to amplify protecting immigrants and ICE out for Good!

Note that this is an active overpass. The goal is to make the banners visible to drivers on 101. If a street protest is what you&apos;re looking for please go to [Marin Action for Protest](https://mailchi.mp/9978b53eb509/crjcb50gck) to find one near year.

_This is a no-host event. An ad hoc group of citizen volunteers are facilitating this opportunity for Marin residents to peacefully and safely assemble in line with their First Amendment rights._

_A core principle behind all Marin protest events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events._

_All participants agree to assume 100% responsibility for their own safety, conduct and well-being. Please review this guide, “How To Protest Safely” in advance: https://www.nrdc.org/stories/how-protest-safely._</p>
