<h3>Tell Target: ICE OUT NOW - Justice for Renee Good &amp; Alex Pretti</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Target - Santa Rosa South (public sidewalks)<br>1980 Santa Rosa Ave<br>Santa Rosa, CA 95404</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Sonoma County</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>ICE OUT OF TARGET
Justice for Renee Good and Alex Pretti

Silence is complicity. It’s time to boycott and protest those corporations that comply with the fascist actions of this regime.
 
**Meet on the public sidewalk, north side of Kawana Springs Road at traffic light at the entrance to the Target store parking lot. This is between Santa Rosa Ave and Petaluma Hill Road.**

Protest on sidewalk, bring signs, whistles, and a friend!

*Why Protest Target?*

ICE Staging Locations in MN - It’s alleged that ICE is using Target parking lots to stage their MN operations

Employees are ICE Victims – Some Target employees are being detained, beaten in at least one case, and sent to detention centers 

Corporate cowardice and silence – Target’s corporate headquarters are located in MN. They have said nothing about the lawless actions being perpetrated by ICE in their hometown. (Note: They signed onto a wholly inadequate letter from a MN Business Leadership organization)

Protest Goals – Target needs to publicly oppose immigration activity on its premises, protect employees, and refuse to cooperate with ICE
.</p>
