<h3>Science Matters Book Club, March</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, March 26, 2026 at 2:00 AM UTC - 4:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Annex<br>247 S Alaska St<br>Palmer, AK 99645</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Mat-Su United for Progress Alaska</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p># 📚 Science Matters Book Club

## March Discussion  
**Featured Book:**  
*[The Icepick Surgeon](https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/55867888-the-icepick-surgeon)* by Sean Kean

Explore the darker side of science with this gripping nonfiction account of crimes, ethical breaches, and moral dilemmas in the pursuit of scientific knowledge. From ancient experiments to modern controversies, Sam Kean reveals the complex human stories behind scientific progress.
**Co-Hosted by Science Matters Book Club and Mat-Su United for Progress**

## 📖 Upcoming Reads
- **April 22:** *Many Things Under a Rock: The Mysteries of Octopuses* — David Scheel  
- **May 27:** *Lab Girl* — Hope Jahren  

**All are welcome!**</p>
