    <Placemark>
        <name>Tell the Indy Airport Authority to Resist ICE Flights</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Tell the Indy Airport Authority to Resist ICE Flights</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 16, 2026 at 5:00 AM UTC - 5:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Westside Indy Indivisible Resistance Movement</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>To the Indianapolis Airport Authority board and senior leadership of the Indianapolis International Airport:

Since July 2025, an average of three ICE deportation flights per week have arrived at the Indianapolis International Airport. These flights are currently operated by Eastern Air Holdings (flying as Eastern Air Express and Eastern Airlines), and are operating in secrecy, hidden from public flight trackers. Once a deportation flight at the airport’s private terminal, dozens of detainees, most of whom appear to be shackled at the wrists and waist, are loaded onto the plane and transported to Alexandria, Louisiana, one of DHS’ primary deportation sites.

At this juncture, your silence on ICE’s use of our airport to traffic our neighbors is no longer acceptable. We, the undersigned organizations and individuals demand that the IAA Board:

1. Publicly condemn ICE’s use of your airport to aid in the human trafficking of our immigrant neighbors.

2. Provide transparency and documentation for ICE operations at your airport, following the lead of airports like Seattle&apos;s King County Airport

3. Allow the press and the public to observe or protest ICE flight operations from the private terminal parking lot.

4. Conduct health and safety checks for detainees, access to mental and medical health care, and proper use of minimal restraints.
Terminate contracts with airport vendors who are collaborating with ICE.  

5. Find safe, legal, and peaceful ways of exercising your bureaucratic oversight to make operations more difficult for the charter companies who have accepted DHS contracts.

Per reporting by multiple news outlets and nonprofit organizations, ICE and DHS officers are committing human rights violations on ICE flights and at ICE detention facilities. Detainees spend 24 to 50 hours on shuffling and deportation flights before the final stop, and will spend all of that time, if not more, in shackles. We have multiple confirmed cases of detainees spending 80+ hours in restraints. By allowing Eastern Air and ICE to operate through Indianapolis Airport, you are complicit in these abuses, and are opening the facility and yourselves to investigation and lawsuits.

Reporting also shows that 74% of the individuals held in ICE detention have no criminal convictions. Many of them are in the process of going through legal immigration or have temporary authority to remain in the US. Once detained, DHS shuffles them around the country in order to isolate them from family and from lawyers trying to defend them. Per the Constitution, non-citizens have constitutional rights to hire legal counsel in deportation cases and receive a fair hearing before a judge. ICE is denying them that right, and they are making the IAA an accessory to this violation.

Respectfully, we ask that you do something, anything, to expose and limit ICE’s use of the Indianapolis International Airport. Show us, show our immigrant communities that you see what’s happening, and that while perhaps you can’t prevent ICE flights from landing, you will not let them happen without condemnation and resistance.

Your continued silence and shrugs are simply complicity.

-Indy Resistance Indivisible, Westside Indianapolis Indivisible Resistance Movement, Indy Action Coalition, Central Indiana DSA, Strong Neighbor, and Indiana Undocumented Youth Alliance</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904859/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
