        <name>Join our Phone Bank: Help frontline communities be heard on extreme weather</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Join our Phone Bank: Help frontline communities be heard on extreme weather</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 18, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 11:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Climate Action Campaign</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Communities in Tampa, FL and Northern Michigan are on the frontlines of extreme weather.

In Florida, families are still recovering from massive climate disasters like Hurricanes Helene and Milton. In Northern Michigan, dangerous ice storms left more than 145,000 homes and businesses without power in sub-freezing temperatures.

In the meantime, we’re seeing the Trump Administration rolling back guardrails on pollution standards and giving big polluters a free pass. 

That’s why, Climate Action Campaign and our partners are organizing  People’s Hearings in both Florida and Michigan to make sure the voices of those directly impacted by extreme weather are heard loud and clear, and to demand stronger climate action from our elected leaders.

We need volunteers to help us reach out to folks in these communities.

Join our phone bank and help recruit community members who’ve lived through these disasters and ensure their stories are heard! We’ll train you on making calls and help you every step of the way!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/896767/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
