        <name>Adopt a Corner: What’s Next? Webinar</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Adopt a Corner: What’s Next? Webinar</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The National Day Laborer Organizing Network (NDLON) is calling on our volunteers to take the next step in supporting our community. Come and make a plan for how to show up in person, nonviolently, with courage, with love, and with urgency for our immigrant neighbors.

Please join us for a training and conversation on “ICE Out of Our Community” on February 18. This session is designed for volunteers who have already joined a day labor corner and want to learn how to escalate their impact, organize their community, and take proactive action for immigrant justice.

What to expect:

1.A recap of the Adopt-a-Corner program and guidance on next steps

2.Strategies to escalate your program and increase volunteer support

3.Tips for growing and organizing your community

4.How to conduct worksite visits and what they look like in practice

5.Best practices for sustaining and scaling your efforts

6.Updates on our volunteer communication platform and how you’ll stay connected moving forward

We’re excited to reconnect with all of you and support your continued work in our communities. Let’s keep building, together.

— The NDLON Organizing Team</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/898198/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
