        <name>Know Your Rights - Interactions with ICE</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Know Your Rights - Interactions with ICE</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 21, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Democratic Party of New Mexico</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This is a training hosted by the New Mexico House Democrats in partnership with ACLU of NM and the NM Immigrant Law Center. The Know Your Rights training is designed to inform citizens and noncitizens alike of their legal rights during interactions with federal law enforcement agencies, what to do if you feel like those rights are being violated, and how to attempt to keep interactions with agents as safe as possible.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/900410/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
