        <name>Sick about ICE Terrorism? Let’s call our elected officials. Mondays, 12PM PST</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Sick about ICE Terrorism? Let’s call our elected officials. Mondays, 12PM PST</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, February 23, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 8:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> CBFD Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Are you upset about the dismantling of our democracy, the violence perpetrated by I.C.E. on innocent people, the theft of millions of Americans’ private information, attacks on healthcare and social security, the Republican intent to take away a woman’s right to vote, and more? Don’t despair - take action!

One easy thing you can do that truly matters is make calls to your elected representatives, to let them know how you feel about an issue and what you expect them to do about it. Maybe you want to call your Member of Congress or your Senators but just haven’t done it yet. You know what you want, but you aren’t sure what to say.

Well, we’ve got a solution - a tool to help you make the calls, and to make your point. It’s also very rewarding because we’re doing it together. Join us every Monday on Zoom beginning January 5, 2026 at Noon Pacific time. We’ll provide all you need to make the calls - phone numbers, scripts, and training.  You’ll just need your phone, or your phone and your computer if you’d like a bigger screen for viewing.
 
We hope to see you on Zoom for this easy, effective action. Thirty minutes is all you’ll need to make sure our electeds know that we’re paying attention and demanding they take action.  There are millions of us across America - our collective voices will make a difference.  We’re in this together!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/893153/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
