        <name>Let&apos;s Talk - Legislative Phone Bank</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Let&apos;s Talk - Legislative Phone Bank</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, February 24, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> TIRRC Votes</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## Join us each week as we call voters across Tennessee to mobilize them to contact their legislators and urge them to stand against bills attacking our communities, our neighbors, and our futures.

*This is a virtual opportunity and training will be provided each shift.*

This Legislative Session, we&apos;re more determined than ever to fight for the rights and freedoms of everyone across Tennessee, whether you were born in Memphis or Mexico, Mountain City or Mozambique. We believe that if you live and are making a life here, Tennessee is your home and you deserve to feel safe and have the resources you need to build a good life for yourself and your family. 

Yet the Republican supermajority is planning to scale up attacks on immigrant neighbors instead of enacting policies Tennesseans actually want and have been asking for for years, such as fully funded schools, no tax on groceries, and affordable healthcare. We deserve a Tennessee where working families come first, where our tax dollars go to our communities instead of the escalation of force from ICE agents against our neighbors.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/898415/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
