        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Q&amp;A with Middleton Officials-Asking the &quot;What ifs&quot; of Immigration Enforcement</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 25, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> WisDems</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>### Join us Tuesday Feb 24th from 7 to 8 pm for our virtual Community Conversation

What is happening in Minneapolis is tragic and on the minds of many.  We want to hear from our local elected officials.   We&apos;ll have a question and answer session with Middleton Mayor Emily Kuhn and Middleton Chief of police Steven Thompson regarding planning and preparing for the &quot;what ifs&quot; of immigration enforcement.  We will review our rights, preparations if ICE comes to Middleton, impact on our community, and other related questions on your mind.</p>
