    <Placemark>
        <name>Community Club Reads: Woodworking</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Community Club Reads: Woodworking</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Vote Save America PAC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The VSA Community Reads book club is back, and this time we’re reading **Woodworking by Emily St. James**! Join some of the kindest, most fun political and book nerds out there to talk about this incredible novel, and how stories like this can help us better understand ourselves, our world, and our politics. Together we’ll also build community ahead of the massively important midterm elections this November. 

**Reading Guide:**
For our book club discussions on Woodworking by Emily St. James, here’s your reading guide:

- Feb 17 (8ET/5PT): Read &quot;September&quot; pgs. 1-69

- Mar 03 (8ET/5PT): Read &quot;October&quot; pgs. 70-250

- Mar 17 (8ET/5PT): Read &quot;November&quot; and &quot;December&quot; pgs. 251-347


**How it works:**
Whether you’ve been to book club before or this is your first time, here’s a quick refresher on how it works. For each one-hour meeting we’ll all read the same section of the book (listed above). Then, on the day of the meeting, you’ll hop on zoom. Together as a big group we’ll do some quick housekeeping and an icebreaker in the chat before we head off into breakout rooms to discuss the book. There, you get to hang out with your fellow VSA-friends for a fun discussion facilitated by a couple of your friendly neighborhood VSA community mods. Finally, we’ll come back together for the last few minutes to recap our discussion before we close. 

To get a copy of the book, head to [bookshop.org](https://bookshop.org/p/books/woodworking-emily-st-james/520f0326fb73f621?ean=9781638931478&amp;next=t&amp;&amp;utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_campaign=dsa_nonbrand&amp;utm_content={adgroupname}&amp;utm_term=aud-1721779758455:dsa-19959388920&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gad_campaignid=12440232635&amp;gbraid=0AAAAACfld42zMPPia9T3wyqSaNYDEzADg&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQiAkPzLBhD4ARIsAGfah8hiIc1S3JqGJD74vDM8hMww-_Oc2K4ylps94Lc4r4VAybUcAzkqGMIaAtYCEALw_wcB), your favorite local independent bookstore or library, or wherever books are sold! 

**About Woodworking by Emily St. James:**
Woodworking is an unforgettable and heartwarming book-club debut following a trans high school teacher from a small town in South Dakota who befriends the only other trans woman she knows: one of her students. Heartwarming, hopeful, and at once wrenching, this is a celebration of intergenerational stories, unlikely friendships, courage, and hope. It doesn’t shy away from the ugliness and hate in the world, but neither does it leave us there - a hopeful tonic in these deeply challenging times.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/896913/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-18T07:03:09.039Z</i></p>
]]></description>
